    "/CONTRIBUTING.md": "# Contributing\n\nTigerPath is an open source project maintained by and for Princeton students.\nIf you would like to help out, you have come to the right place!\n\nYou can contribute in any of a number of ways:\n\n## Bug Reports and Feature Requests\n\nThis is the easiest way to contribute, and you do not need any technical know-how.\nJust go to the [issues](https://github.com/PrincetonUSG/TigerPath/issues) page and tap \"New Issue\" at the top right of the page.\n\nYou can file a\n[**Bug Report**](https://github.com/PrincetonUSG/TigerPath/issues/new?assignees=&labels=bug&template=bug_report.md&title=)\nif you find a problem with the app. To help us find a solution, describe how you found the problem,\nand, if relevant, provide a screenshot or link (for instance to a relevant department web page) that helps us see the problem.\n\nIf you have an idea for how to improve the app, you can also file a\n[**Feature Request**](https://github.com/PrincetonUSG/TigerPath/issues/new?assignees=&labels=enhancement&template=feature_request.md&title=)\nat the same place. Describe how you envision\nthe app improving and how you think it will help users, including yourself.\n\nIf you don't have anything in mind, you can still help by reading through the issues page and adding your thoughts on the issues\nothers have posted. Do you have the same problem they do? Do you like their idea? Do you think there is a better way? Feel\nfree to engage in conversations about the best way to improve TigerPath.\n\n## Adding or editing major and certificate requirements\n\nMajor, certificate, and departmental data were moved to another repository in December 2022. [Visit the repository](https://github.com/PrincetonUSG/Princeton-Departmental-Data) to learn how to contribute!\n\n## Contributing Code\n\nThis is only for the more technically savvy among you who would like to take on an extra challenge with the goal of helping to\nimprove the experiences of our student users.\n\nIf you would like to implement a new feature, first open an issue so that it can be discussed and we can come to a shared\nconsensus of how this feature will come about.\n\nSecond, either start a new feature branch or fork the repository and start a branch there, and implement your new feature in\nthis feature branch. Take a look at the [README](https://github.com/PrincetonUSG/TigerPath/blob/master/README.md)\nfor some help with setting up an environment with which to test your local changes.\n\nOnce you are satisfied with your changes, come back to the TigerPath GitHub and submit a pull request to the `master`\nbranch of TigerHub (the branch that goes into production).\n\nThere we will together discuss your changes and if anything needs to be ammended. If everything looks good, we will then\nmerge your code into the `master` branch and deploy it to [tigerpath.io](https://www.tigerpath.io/).\n\nFeel free to reach out to us through GitHub at any point to ask for help with your contributions, or reach out directly by\nemail to Barak Nehoran (netid: bnehoran).\n\n## Thanks!\n\nSince this is a project that is maintained and supported by a community of Princeton students, it is only as good\nas the students contributers would like it to be.\n\nOn behalf of the thousands of Princeton students who use TigerPath, thanks for helping to make it a better, more accurate,\nand more user-friendly tool for ourselves and for the next generation of students.",

    "/README.md": "# TigerPath\n\nTigerPath is a web app that helps Princeton University students plan out their four-year course schedules. It began as a COS 333 project by Richard Chu, Barak Nehoran, Adeniji Ogunlana, and Daniel Leung.\n\nYou can visit TigerPath at [tigerpath.io](https://www.tigerpath.io).\n\nTo learn about contributing to TigerPath, take a look at the [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/PrincetonUSG/TigerPath/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n# Running locally\n\n## Initial setup\n\n### Python environment\n\n1. Create a new conda environment: `conda create -n tigerpath`\n1. Activate the conda environment: `conda activate tigerpath`\n1. Install python: `conda install python=3.9`\n1. Clone this repo and `cd` into the base TigerPath directory\n1. Install dependencies: `pip install -r requirements.txt`\n   - If you're running into a `psycopg2` error (`pg_config executable not found`), you probably have to install `postgresql`: https://stackoverflow.com/a/24645416\n1. Run `conda list` to validate that all packages in `requirements.txt` were installed\n1. Set all environment variables:\n   - Login to Heroku and go to the Settings tab for the `tigerpath333-dev` app (do NOT use prod!)\n   - Reveal Config Vars\n   - For each Config Var key-value pair, create a local environment variable: `conda env config vars set key=value` (replace `key` and `value` with the actual key and value)\n   - After setting all env vars, reactivate your conda environment: `conda activate tigerpath`\n   - Note that for `SECRET_KEY`, you might get an error so you can set its value to `1`\n1. Run `conda env config vars list` to validate all env vars were set\n\n### Node packages\n\n1. Run `cd frontend && npm install` to install all required frontend packages\n   - You might have to install `node` if you haven't already: https://formulae.brew.sh/formula/node\n\n## Running the dev server\n\nAfter following the initial setup steps above, you can run the local development server:\n\n1. Activate your environment: `conda activate tigerpath`\n1. Run the backend server: `python manage.py runserver`\n1. Run the frontend server in a separate terminal window: `cd frontend && npm start`\n   - Visit `http://localhost:8000/` to verify the server is up and running\n\n# Other important things\n\n#### Make migrations and update database\n\nYou can do this by running the following commands:\n\n```\npython manage.py makemigrations                             # Makes migrations based on models.py\npython manage.py migrate                                    # Migrates the database\n```\n\n#### Custom django-admin commands\n\n```\npython manage.py tigerpath_get_courses                      # Scrapes courses and puts them in the database\n```\n\n#### Load static data\n\nTo load the major mappings fixture, which populates the major table in the database, run the following command:\n\n```\npython manage.py loaddata major_mappings\n```",

scraper\n# Term numbering system:\n#   First digit: always a 1 -- not clear why\n#   Second and Third digits: last 2 digits of ending year of schoolyear\n#   Fourth digit: the season number, as follows\n#     1 = Summer\n#     2 = Fall\n#     3 = Winter\n#     4 = Spring\n#   Usually only 2 (Fall) and 4 (Spring) are used.\n#\n# For example, the Fall 2016 term is 1172 - the ending year is 2017.\n# Similarly, the Spring 2017 term is 1174 - the ending year is 2017.\n#\n# By convention, we keep the 8 most recent semesters in this array.\n# Please update this array if you are scraping for new courses.\n# ACTIVE_TERMS = MobileApp().get_active_term_codes(n_recent_terms=8)\nACTIVE_TERMS = [1252, 1244, 1242, 1234, 1232, 1224, 1222, 1214]",

    "/frontend/config/env.js": "'use strict';\n\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst paths = require('./paths');\n\n// Make sure that including paths.js after env.js will read .env variables.\ndelete require.cache[require.resolve('./paths')];\n\nconst NODE_ENV = process.env.NODE_ENV;\nif (!NODE_ENV) {\n  throw new Error(\n    'The NODE_ENV environment variable is required but was not specified.'\n  );\n}\n\n// https://github.com/bkeepers/dotenv#what-other-env-files-can-i-use\nvar dotenvFiles = [\n  `${paths.dotenv}.${NODE_ENV}.local`,\n  `${paths.dotenv}.${NODE_ENV}`,\n  // Don't include `.env.local` for `test` environment\n  // since normally you expect tests to produce the same\n  // results for everyone\n  NODE_ENV !== 'test' && `${paths.dotenv}.local`,\n  paths.dotenv,\n].filter(Boolean);\n\n// Load environment variables from .env* files. Suppress warnings using silent\n// if this file is missing. dotenv will never modify any environment variables\n// that have already been set.  Variable expansion is supported in .env files.\n// https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv\n// https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv-expand\ndotenvFiles.forEach(dotenvFile => {\n  if (fs.existsSync(dotenvFile)) {\n    require('dotenv-expand')(\n      require('dotenv').config({\n        path: dotenvFile,\n      })\n    );\n  }\n});\n\n// We support resolving modules according to `NODE_PATH`.\n// This lets you use absolute paths in imports inside large monorepos:\n// https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/issues/253.\n// It works similar to `NODE_PATH` in Node itself:\n// https://nodejs.org/api/modules.html#modules_loading_from_the_global_folders\n// Note that unlike in Node, only *relative* paths from `NODE_PATH` are honored.\n// Otherwise, we risk importing Node.js core modules into an app instead of Webpack shims.\n// https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/issues/1023#issuecomment-265344421\n// We also resolve them to make sure all tools using them work consistently.\nconst appDirectory = fs.realpathSync(process.cwd());\nprocess.env.NODE_PATH = (process.env.NODE_PATH || '')\n  .split(path.delimiter)\n  .filter(folder => folder && !path.isAbsolute(folder))\n  .map(folder => path.resolve(appDirectory, folder))\n  .join(path.delimiter);\n\n// Grab NODE_ENV and REACT_APP_* environment variables and prepare them to be\n// injected into the application via DefinePlugin in Webpack configuration.\nconst REACT_APP = /^REACT_APP_/i;\n\nfunction getClientEnvironment(publicUrl) {\n  const raw = Object.keys(process.env)\n    .filter(key => REACT_APP.test(key))\n    .reduce(\n      (env, key) => {\n        env[key] = process.env[key];\n        return env;\n      },\n      {\n        // Useful for determining whether we\u2019re running in production mode.\n        // Most importantly, it switches React into the correct mode.\n        NODE_ENV: process.env.NODE_ENV || 'development',\n        // Useful for resolving the correct path to static assets in `public`.\n        // For example, <img src={process.env.PUBLIC_URL + '/img/logo.png'} />.\n        // This should only be used as an escape hatch. Webpack build.\n    new SWPrecacheWebpackPlugin({\n      // By default, a cache-busting query parameter is appended to requests\n      // used to populate the caches, to ensure the responses are fresh.\n      // If a URL is already hashed by Webpack, then there is no concern\n      // about it being stale, and the cache-busting can be skipped.\n      dontCacheBustUrlsMatching: /\\.\\w{8}\\./,\n      filename: 'service-worker.js',\n      logger(message) {\n        if (message.indexOf('Total precache size is') === 0) {\n          // This message occurs for every build and is a bit too noisy.\n          return;\n        }\n        if (message.indexOf('Skipping static resource') === 0) {\n          // This message obscures real errors so we ignore it.\n          // https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/issues/2612\n          return;\n        }\n        console.log(message);\n      },\n      minify: true,\n      // For unknown URLs, fallback to the index page\n      navigateFallback: publicUrl + '/index.html',\n      // Ignores URLs starting from /__ (useful for Firebase):\n      // https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/issues/2237#issuecomment-302693219\n      navigateFallbackWhitelist: [/^(?!\\/__).*/],\n      // Don't precache sourcemaps (they're large) and build asset manifest:\n      staticFileGlobsIgnorePatterns: [/\\.map$/, /asset-manifest\\.json$/],\n    }),\n    new BundleTracker({\n      path: paths.statsRoot,\n      filename: 'webpack-stats.prod.json',\n    }),\n    // Moment.js is an extremely popular library that bundles large locale files\n    // by default due to how Webpack interprets its code. This is a practical\n    // solution that requires the user to opt into importing specific locales.\n    // https://github.com/jmblog/how-to-optimize-momentjs-with-webpack\n    // You can remove this if you don't use Moment.js:\n    new webpack.IgnorePlugin(/^\\.\\/locale$/, /moment$/),\n  ],\n  optimization: {\n    minimizer: [\n      new UglifyJsPlugin({\n        uglifyOptions: {\n          warnings: false,\n          output: {\n            comments: false,\n          },\n        },\n        sourceMap: shouldUseSourceMap,\n      }),\n    ],\n  },\n  // Some libraries import Node modules but don't use them in the browser.\n  // Tell Webpack to provide empty mocks for them so importing them works.\n  node: {\n    dgram: 'empty',\n    fs: 'empty',\n    net: 'empty',\n    tls: 'empty',\n    child_process: 'empty',\n  },\n};",
    "/frontend/config/webpackDevServer.config.js": "'use strict';\n\nconst errorOverlayMiddleware = require('react-dev-utils/errorOverlayMiddleware');\nconst noopServiceWorkerMiddleware = require('react-dev-utils/noopServiceWorkerMiddleware');\nconst ignoredFiles = require('react-dev-utils/ignoredFiles');\nconst config = require('./webpack.config.dev');\nconst paths = require('./paths');\n\nconst protocol = process.env.HTTPS === 'true' ? 'https' : 'http';\nconst host = process.env.HOST || '0.0.0.0';\n\nmodule.exports = function (proxy, allowedHost) {\n  return {\n    // WebpackDevServer 2.4.3 introduced a security fix that prevents remote\n    // websites from potentially accessing local content through DNS rebinding:\n    // https://github.com/webpack/webpack-dev-server/issues/887\n    // https://medium.com/webpack/webpack-dev-server-middleware-security-issues-1489d950874a\n    // However, it made several existing use cases such as development in cloud\n    // environment or subdomains in development significantly more complicated:\n    // https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/issues/2271\n    // https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/issues/2233\n    // While we're investigating better solutions, for now we will take a\n    // compromise. Since our WDS configuration only serves files in the `public`\n    // folder we won't consider accessing them a vulnerability. However, if you\n    // use the `proxy` feature, it gets more dangerous because it can expose\n    // remote code execution vulnerabilities in backends like Django and Rails.\n    // So we will disable the host check normally, but enable it if you have\n    // specified the `proxy` setting. Finally, we let you override it if you\n    // really know what you're doing with a special environment variable.\n    disableHostCheck:\n      !proxy || process.env.DANGEROUSLY_DISABLE_HOST_CHECK === 'true',\n    // Enable gzip compression of generated files.\n    compress: true,\n    // Silence WebpackDevServer's own logs since they're generally not useful.\n    // It will still show compile warnings and errors with this setting.\n    clientLogLevel: 'none',\n    // By default WebpackDevServer serves physical files from current directory\n    // in addition to all the virtual build products that it serves from memory.\n    // This is confusing because those files won\u2019t automatically be available in\n    // production build folder unless we copy them. However, copying the whole\n    // project directory is dangerous because we may expose sensitive files.\n    // Instead, we establish a convention that only files in `public` directory\n    // get served. Our build script will copy `public` into the `build` folder.\n    // In `index.html`, you can get URL of `public` folder with %PUBLIC_URL%:\n    // <link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"%PUBLIC_URL%/favicon.ico\">\n    // In JavaScript code, you can access it with `process.env.PUBLIC_URL`.\n    // Note that we only recommend to use `public` folder as an escape hatch\n    // for files like `favicon.ico`, `manifest.json`, and libraries that are\n    // for some reason broken when imported through Webpack. If you just want to\n    // use an image, put it in `src` and `import` it from JavaScript instead.\n    contentBase: paths.appPublic,\n    // By default files from `contentBase` will not trigger a page reload.\n    watchContentBase: true,\n    // Enable hot reloading server. It will provide /sockjs-node/ endpoint\n    // for the WebpackDevServer client so it can learn when the files were\n    // updated. The WebpackDevServer client is included as an entry point\n    // in the Webpack development configuration. Note that only changes\n    // to CSS are currently hot reloaded. JS changes will refresh the browser.\n    hot: true,\n    // It is important to tell WebpackDevServer to use the same \"root\" path\n    // as we specified in the config. In development, we always serve from /.\n    publicPath: config.output.publicPath,\n    // WebpackDevServer is noisy by default so we emit custom message instead\n    // by listening to the compiler events with `compiler.plugin` calls above.\n    quiet: true,\n    // Reportedly, this avoids CPU overload on some systems.\n    // https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/issues/293\n    // src/node_modules is not ignored to support absolute imports\n    // https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/issues/1065\n    watchOptions: {\n      ignored: ignoredFiles(paths.appSrc),\n    },\n    // Enable HTTPS if the HTTPS environment variable is set to 'true'\n    https: protocol === 'https',\n    host: host,\n    headers: {\n      'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': '*',\n    },\n    overlay: false,\n    historyApiFallback: {\n      // Paths with dots should still use the history fallback.\n      // See https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/issues/387.\n      disableDotRule: true,\n    },\n    public: allowedHost,\n    proxy,\n    before(app) {\n      // This lets us open files from the runtime error overlay.\n      app.use(errorOverlayMiddleware());\n      // This service worker file is effectively a 'no-op' that will reset any\n      // previous service worker registered for the same host:port combination.\n      // We do this in development to avoid hitting the production cache if\n      // it used the same host and port.\n      // https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/issues/2272#issuecomment-302832432\n      app.use(noopServiceWorkerMiddleware(''));\n    },\n  };\n};",

    "/frontend/src/AjaxSetup.js": "import $ from 'jquery';\n\n// setting up ajax request with csrf\nfunction getCookie(name) {\n  var cookieValue = null;\n  if (document.cookie && document.cookie !== '') {\n    var cookies = document.cookie.split(';');\n    for (var i = 0; i < cookies.length; i++) {\n      var cookie = $.trim(cookies[i]);\n      // Does this cookie string begin with the name we want?\n      if (cookie.substring(0, name.length + 1) === name + '=') {\n        cookieValue = decodeURIComponent(cookie.substring(name.length + 1));\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  return cookieValue;\n}\n\nfunction csrfSafeMethod(method) {\n  // these HTTP methods do not require CSRF protection\n  return /^(GET|HEAD|OPTIONS|TRACE)$/.test(method);\n}\n\nexport function ajaxSetup() {\n  let csrftoken = getCookie('csrftoken');\n  $.ajaxSetup({\n    beforeSend: function (xhr, settings) {\n      if (!csrfSafeMethod(settings.type) && !this.crossDomain) {\n        xhr.setRequestHeader('X-CSRFToken', csrftoken);\n      }\n    },\n  });\n}",
    "/frontend/src/Popover.js": "import $ from 'jquery';\nimport {\n  getSemesterType,\n  isFallSemester,\n  isSpringSemester,\n  convertSemToTermCode,\n} from 'utils/SemesterUtils';\n\n// TODO: refactor from here and SearchCard.js\nconst BASE_COURSE_OFFERINGS_URL = 'https://www.princetoncourses.com/course/';\n\nexport function addPopover(course, courseKey, semIndex) {\n  let courseName = course['name'];\n  let courseTitle = course['title'];\n  let courseSemType = course['semester'];\n\n  let courseElement = $(`#${courseKey}`);\n  courseElement.attr('title', courseName);\n  courseElement.attr('data-html', 'true');\n\n  // Add content to the popover\n  let content;\n  if (!course['external']) {\n    content = courseTitle;\n  } else {\n    content = \"This is an external credit that you've added.\";\n  }\n  let addedCoursesWithSameName = $('.semester').find(`[title=\"${courseName}\"]`);\n\n  if (addedCoursesWithSameName.length > 1) {\n    content +=\n      \"<div class='popover-warning'>This course has already been added to your schedule.</div>\";\n  }\n\n  if (courseSemType === 'fall' && isSpringSemester(getSemesterType(semIndex))) {\n    content +=\n      \"<div class='popover-warning'>This course has previously only been offered in the Fall.</div>\";\n  } else if (\n    courseSemType === 'spring' &&\n    isFallSemester(getSemesterType(semIndex))\n  ) {\n    content +=\n      \"<div class='popover-warning'>This course has previously only been offered in the Spring.</div>\";\n  }\n\n  let courseId = course['id'];\n  // TODO: Don't hardcode the semester list\n  let courseSemList = course['semester_list'];\n  if (courseSemList && courseSemList.length > 0) {\n    let termCode = convertSemToTermCode(\n      courseSemList[courseSemList.length - 1]\n    );\n    let courseInfoLink = BASE_COURSE_OFFERINGS_URL + termCode + courseId;\n\n    content += \"<div className='search-card-links'>\";\n    content +=\n      '<a href=' +\n      courseInfoLink +\n      \" target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'> \";\n    content += \"<i class='fas fa-info-circle fa-lg fa-fw course-info'></i>\";\n    content += '</a> ';\n    content += '</div>';\n  }\n\n  courseElement.attr('data-content', content);\n\n  // Show the popover when it's hovered over\n  courseElement\n    .popover({\n      trigger: 'manual',\n      html: true,\n      animation: true,\n      sanitize: false,\n    })\n    .on('mouseenter', () => {\n      courseElement.popover('show');\n      $('.popover').on('mouseleave', () => {\n        courseElement.popover('hide');\n      });\n    })\n    .on('mouseleave', () => {\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        if (!$('.popover:hover').length) {\n          courseElement.popover('hide');\n        }\n      }, 100);\n    });\n}",
    "/frontend/src/components/App.js": "import React, { Component } from 'react';\nimport $ from 'jquery';\nimport { ajaxSetup } from 'AjaxSetup';\nimport Search from 'components/Search';\nimport MainView from 'components/MainView';\nimport Requirements from 'components/Requirements';\nimport { DragDropContext } from 'react-beautiful-dnd';\nimport { ThemeProvider } from constructor(props) {\n    super(props);\n    ajaxSetup();\n    this.state = {\n      profile: null,\n      schedule: null,\n      requirements: null,\n      searchQuery: '',\n      searchResults: [],\n    };\n  }\n\n  componentDidMount() {\n    this.fetchProfile();\n    this.fetchRequirements();\n  }\n\n  componentDidUpdate(prevProps, prevState) {\n    if (this.state.schedule !== prevState.schedule) {\n      if (prevState.schedule !== null) {\n        this.updateScheduleAndGetRequirements();\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  fetchProfile = () => {\n    $.ajax({\n      url: '/api/v1/get_profile/',\n      datatype: 'json',\n      type: 'GET',\n      success: (profile) => this.setState({ profile }),\n    });\n  };\n\n  // gets current enrolled courses and sends post request\n  updateScheduleAndGetRequirements = () => {\n    let schedule = this.state.schedule;\n    let strippedSchedule = [];\n    for (let semIndex = 0; semIndex < schedule.length; semIndex++) {\n      strippedSchedule.push([]);\n      for (let course of schedule[semIndex]) {\n        let strippedCourse = { id: course['id'], settled: course['settled'] };\n        if (course['external']) {\n          strippedCourse['external'] = course['external'];\n          strippedCourse['name'] = course['name'];\n        }\n        strippedSchedule[semIndex].push(strippedCourse);\n      }\n    }\n\n    $.ajax({\n      url: '/api/v1/update_schedule_and_get_requirements/',\n      type: 'POST',\n      data: { schedule: JSON.stringify(strippedSchedule) },\n      success: (data) => this.handleRequirementData(data),\n    });\n  };\n\n  fetchRequirements = () => {\n    $.ajax({\n      url: '/api/v1/get_requirements/',\n      datatype: 'json',\n      type: 'GET',\n      success: (data) => this.handleRequirementData(data),\n    });\n  };\n\n  handleRequirementData = (data) => {\n    if (data) {\n      // there are 3 fields to the data output, the 2nd indexed field contains the requirements json which we display\n      data = data.map((mainReq) => {\n        // if mainReq is not an array, then it is just the name of the major\n        if (!Array.isArray(mainReq)) return mainReq;\n        return mainReq[2];\n      });\n      this.setState({ requirements: data });\n    }\n  };\n\n  onDragEnd = (result) => {\n    let schedule = (this.state.schedule || DEFAULT_SCHEDULE).slice();\n    let searchResults = this.state.searchResults;\n\n    if (result.destination === null) return;\n\n    let destSemId = parseInt(\n      result.destination.droppableId.split('sem')[1],\n      RADIX\n    );\n    let destCourseIndex = result.destination.index;\n    let sourceCourseIndex = result.source.index;\n\n    if (result.source.droppableId.includes('search-result-droppable')) {\n      // moving course from search results to schedule\n      let searchResultsCourse = searchResults[sourceCourseIndex];\n      let course = {};\n      course['id'] = searchResultsCourse['id'];\n      course['name'] = searchResultsCourse['name'];\n      course['title'] = searchResultsCourse['title'];\n      course['dist_area'] = searchResultsCourse['dist_area'];\n      course['semester'] = searchResultsCourse['semester'];\n      course['semester_list'] = searchResultsCourse['semester_list'];\n      course['settled'] = [];\n      schedule[destSemId].splice(destCourseIndex, 0, course);\n    } else {\n      // moving course between or within semesters\n      let sourceSemId = parseInt(\n        result.source.droppableId.split('sem')[1],\n        RADIX\n      );\n      let course = schedule[sourceSemId].splice(sourceCourseIndex, 1)[0];\n      schedule[destSemId].splice(destCourseIndex, 0, course);\n    }\n\n    this.setState({ schedule: schedule });\n  };\n\n  onChange = (name, value) => this.setState({ [name]: value });\n\n  render() {\n    return (\n      <ThemeProvider theme={TIGERPATH_THEME}>\n        <React.Fragment>\n          <h1 className=\"print-only\">My Four Year Schedule</h1>\n          <p className=\"print-only\">\n            This schedule was created using{' '}\n            <b>TigerPath - Princeton's Four-Year Course Planner</b> at{' '}\n            <a\n              href=\"http://www.tigerpath.io/\"\n              target=\"_blank\"\n              rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\n            >\n              tigerpath.io\n            </a>\n            .\n          </p>\n          <DragDropContext onDragEnd={this.onDragEnd}>\n            <div id=\"search-pane\" className=\"col-lg-2 pl-0 pr-0 dont-print\">\n              <Search\n                onChange={this.onChange}\n                searchQuery={this.state.searchQuery}\n                searchResults={this.state.searchResults}\n              />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"col-lg-8 pl-0 pr-0\">\n              <MainView\n                onChange={this.onChange}\n                profile={this.state.profile}\n                schedule={this.state.schedule}\n                requirements={this.state.requirements}\n              />\n            </div>\n          </DragDropContext>\n          <div className=\"col-lg-2 pl-0 pr-0 break dont-print\">\n            <Requirements\n              onChange={this.onChange}\n              requirements={this.state.requirements}\n              schedule={this.state.schedule}\n            />\n          </div>\n        </React.Fragment>\n      </ThemeProvider>\n    );\n  }\n}",
    "/frontend/src/components/CourseCard.js": "import React, { Component } from 'react';\nimport $ from 'jquery';\nimport { Draggable } from 'react-beautiful-dnd';\nimport { EXTERNAL_CREDITS_SEMESTER_INDEX } from 'utils/SemesterUtils';\n\nexport default class CourseCard extends Component {\n  removeCourse = () => {\n    this.props.onCourseRemove(this.props.semIndex, this.props.courseIndex);\n    $(`#${this.props.courseKey}`).popover('hide');\n  };\n\n  getClassNames = (isDragging) => {\n    let classNames = [];\n    classNames.push('course-card');\n    classNames.push(this.props.course['semester']);\n    if (isDragging) classNames.push('course-card-shadow');\n    return classNames.join(' ');\n  };\n\n  render() {\n    let { course, courseKey, courseIndex, semIndex } = this.props;\n    return (\n      <div className=\"unbreakable\">\n        <Draggable\n          draggableId={courseKey}\n          index={courseIndex}\n          isDragDisabled={semIndex === EXTERNAL_CREDITS_SEMESTER_INDEX}\n        >\n          {(provided, snapshot) => (\n            <div\n              ref={provided.innerRef}\n              id={courseKey}\n              title={course['name']}\n              className={this.getClassNames(snapshot.isDragging)}\n              {...provided.draggableProps}\n              {...provided.dragHandleProps}\n            >\n              <div className=\"course-name\">{course['name']}</div>\n              <i\n                className=\"fas fa-times-circle delete-course\"\n                onClick={this.removeCourse}\n              />\n            </div>\n          )}\n        </Draggable>\n        <div className=\"search-card-info print-only\">{course['title']}</div>\n      </div>\n    );\n  }\n}",

Symbol('formSuccess'),\n});\n\nexport default class ExternalCreditForm extends Component {\n  constructor(props) {\n    super(props);\n    this.state = {\n      name: DEFAULT_NAME,\n      selectedSemester: null,\n      selectedRequirement: null,\n      formState: FORM_STATE.NOT_SUBMITTED,\n    };\n  }\n\n  handleChange = (stateName, eventLabel, eventKey) => {\n    this.setState({ [stateName]: { label: eventLabel, value: eventKey } });\n  };\n\n  handleSubmit = (event) => {\n    const form = event.currentTarget;\n\n    // check to see that the form has been completely filled out\n    if (\n      form.checkValidity() === false ||\n      !this.state.selectedSemester ||\n      !this.state.selectedRequirement\n    ) {\n      this.setState({ formState: FORM_STATE.FAILURE });\n      event.preventDefault();\n      event.stopPropagation();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    let schedule = (this.props.schedule || DEFAULT_SCHEDULE).slice();\n    let semIndex = this.state.selectedSemester.value;\n\n    // populate the course values\n    let course = {};\n    course['id'] = uuidv1();\n    course['external'] = true;\n    course['name'] = this.state.name.value;\n    course['dist_area'] = null;\n    course['semester'] = 'external';\n    course['settled'] = [this.state.selectedRequirement.value];\n\n    // add the course to the schedule\n    let scheduleSemester;\n    if (semIndex === 'N/A') {\n      scheduleSemester = schedule[EXTERNAL_CREDITS_SEMESTER_INDEX];\n    } else {\n      scheduleSemester = schedule[semIndex];\n formState: FORM_STATE.SUCCESS,\n      name: DEFAULT_NAME,\n      selectedSemester: null,\n      selectedRequirement: null,\n    });\n\n    event.preventDefault();\n  };\n\n  render() {\n    let = this.state.name;\n\n    return (\n      <div className={this.props.className}>\n        <Card>\n          <ECCardHeader>Add external credit</ECCardHeader>\n          <Card.Body>\n            <Alert\n              variant=\"success\"\n              show={this.state.formState === FORM_STATE.SUCCESS}\n              onClose={() =>\n                this.setState({ formState: FORM_STATE.NOT_SUBMITTED })\n              }\n              dismissible={true}\n            >\n              Your external credit has been successfully created!\n            </Alert>\n            <Alert\n              variant=\"danger\"\n              show={this.state.formState === FORM_STATE.FAILURE}\n              onClose={() =>\n                this.setState({ formState: FORM_STATE.NOT_SUBMITTED })\n              }\n              dismissible={true}\n            >\n              Please fill out all of the fields.\n            </Alert>\n\n            <Form <OverlayTrigger\n                    placement=\"top\"\n                    overlay={\n                      <Tooltip>\n                        For AP credits, waivers, or other external credits that\n                        don't fit in a semester, choose \"N/A\" - they will appear\n                        in \"Your External Credits\" on the left. For a summer\n                        course, choose either the semester before or after the\n                        summer in which you took it.\n                      </Tooltip>\n                    }\n                  >\n                    <i className=\"fas fa-info-circle fa-lg fa-fw ml-1\" />\n                  </OverlayTrigger>\n                </Form.Label>\n                <SemesterDropdown>\n                  <Dropdown.Toggle variant=\"secondary\">\n                    {semesterDropdownLabel}\n                  </Dropdown.Toggle>\n                  <Dropdown.Menu>\n                    <Dropdown.Item\n                      eventKey=\"N/A\"\n                      onSelect={(e) =>\n                        this.handleChange('selectedSemester', 'N/A', e)\n                      }\n                    >\n                      N/A\n                    </Dropdown.Item>\n                    {profile &&\n                      profile.classYear &&\n                      getSemesterNames(profile.classYear).map(\n                        (semName, index) => (\n                          <Dropdown.Item\n                            key={semName}\n                            eventKey={index}\n                            onSelect={(e) =>\n                              this.handleChange('selectedSemester', semName, e)\n                            }\n                          >\n                            {semName}\n                          </Dropdown.Item>\n                        )\n                      )}\n                  </Dropdown.Menu>\n                </SemesterDropdown>\n              </Form.Group>\n\n              <Submit variant=\"primary\" type=\"submit\">\n                Submit\n              </Submit>\n            </Form>\n          </Card.Body>\n        </Card>\n      </div>\n    );\n  }\n}",

    "/frontend/src/components/Requirements.js": "import React, { Component } from 'react';\nimport $ from 'jquery';\nimport 'react-treeview/react-treeview.css';\nimport TreeView from 'react-treeview/lib/react-treeview.js';\n\nexport default class Requirements extends Component {\n  componentDidUpdate(prevProps) {\n    if (this.props.requirements !== prevProps.requirements) {\n      this.makeNodesClickable();\n      this.addReqPopovers();\n    }\n  }\n\n  // makes the entire node (not just the arrow) clickable to collapse/uncollapse a node\n  // removes arrows added by library (their listeners cause bugs) and readd them\n  makeNodesClickable = () => {\n    // arrows kept getting deleted when updating for some reason, this makes sure they stay\n    $('.tree-view_arrow').not('.my-arrow').remove();\n    $('.my-arrow').addClass('tree-view_arrow');\n    $('.tree-view_item').each(function () {\n      $(this)\n        .unbind()\n        .click(function () {\n          let arrowCollapsedClass = 'tree-view_arrow-collapsed';\n          let treeCollapsedClass = 'tree-view_children-collapsed';\n          let arrowItem = $(this).find('.tree-view_arrow');\n          if (arrowItem.hasClass(arrowCollapsedClass)) {\n            arrowItem.removeClass(arrowCollapsedClass);\n            $(this)\n              .parent()\n              .find('.tree-view_children')\n              .removeClass(treeCollapsedClass);\n          } else {\n            arrowItem.addClass(arrowCollapsedClass);\n            $(this)\n              .parent()\n              .find('.tree-view_children')\n              .addClass(treeCollapsedClass);\n          }\n        });\n    });\n  };\n\n  getReqCourses = (req_path) => {\n    var searchQuery = 'Satisfying: ' + req_path.split('//').pop();\n    this.props.onChange('searchQuery', searchQuery);\n    $('#spinner').css('display', 'inline-block');\n    $.ajax({\n      // the slashes messes up the url\n      url: '/api/v1/get_req_courses/' + req_path.replace(/\\/\\//g, '$'),\n      datatype: 'json',\n      type: 'GET',\n      cache: true,\n      success: (searchResults) => {\n        this.props.onChange('searchResults', searchResults);\n        $('#spinner').css('display', 'none');\n      },\n    });\n  };\n\n  // adds popovers to reqs\n  addReqPopovers = () => {\n    $('.reqLabel').each((index, reqLabel) => {\n      let reqLabelElement = $(reqLabel);\n      // show popover when it's hovered over\n      reqLabelElement\n        .popover({\n          trigger: 'manual',\n          html: true,\n          animation: true,\n          boundary: 'viewport',\n          template:\n            '<div class=\"popover req-popover\" role=\"tooltip\"><div class=\"arrow\"></div><h3 class=\"popover-header\"></h3><div class=\"popover-body\"></div></div>',\n          sanitize: false,\n        })\n        .on('mouseenter', () => {\n          reqLabelElement.popover('show');\n          $('body')\n            .off('click', '.searchByReq')\n            .on('click', '.searchByReq', () => {\n              this.getReqCourses(reqLabelElement.attr('reqpath'));\n            });\n          $('.popover').on('mouseleave', () => {\n            reqLabelElement.popover('hide');\n          });\n        })\n        .on('mouseleave', () => {\n          setTimeout(() => {\n            if (!$('.popover:hover').length) {\n              reqLabelElement.popover('hide');\n            }\n          }, 100);\n        });\n    });\n  };\n\n  // settles course and runs verifier to update\n  toggleSettle = (course, pathTo, settle) => {\n    let pathToType = pathTo.split('//', 3).join('//');\n    let schedule = this.props.schedule.slice();\n\n    semLoop: for (let sem_num = 0; sem_num < schedule.length; sem_num++) {\n      for (\n        let course_index = 0;\n        course_index < schedule[sem_num].length;\n        course_index++\n      ) {\n        let scheduleCourse = schedule[sem_num][course_index];\n\n        if (scheduleCourse['name'] === course && !scheduleCourse['external']) {\n          let settledReqTypes = scheduleCourse['settled'].map((path) =>\n            path.split('//', 3).join('//')\n          );\n          let indexOfPathToType = settledReqTypes.indexOf(pathToType);\n\n          if (indexOfPathToType === -1 && settle) {\n            scheduleCourse['settled'].push(pathTo);\n            break semLoop;\n          } else if (indexOfPathToType !== -1 && !settle) {\n            scheduleCourse['settled'].splice(indexOfPathToType, 1);\n            break semLoop;\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    this.props.onChange('schedule', schedule);\n  };\n\n  // traverses req tree to display when updating reqlist\n  populateReqTree = (reqTree) => {\n    return reqTree['req_list'].map((requirement, index) => {\n      let finished = '';\n      if (\n        (requirement['min_needed'] === 0 && requirement['count'] >= 0) ||\n        (requirement['min_needed'] > 0 &&\n          requirement['count'] >= requirement['min_needed'])\n      ) {\n        finished = 'req-done';\n      }\n      if (requirement['count'] === 0 && requirement['min_needed'] === 0)\n        finished = 'req-neutral';\n\n      let tag = '';\n      if (requirement['min_needed'] === 0) tag = requirement['count'];\n      else tag = requirement['count'] + '/' + requirement['min_needed'];\n\n      let popoverContent =\n        '<button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-light btn-sm btn-block searchByReq\"><i class=\"fa fa-search\"></i>Find Satisfying Courses</button>';\n      popoverContent += '<div class=\"popoverContentContainer\">';\n      if (requirement.explanation) {\n        popoverContent +=\n          '<p>' + requirement.explanation.split('\\n').join('<br>') + '</p>';\n      }\n      popoverContent += '</div>';\n\n      let reqLabel = (\n        <div\n          className=\"reqLabel\"\n          reqpath={requirement['path_to']}\n          title={'<span>' + requirement['name'] + '</span>'}\n          data-content={popoverContent}\n        >\n          <div className=\"my-arrow\"></div>\n          <span className=\"reqName\">{requirement['name']}</span>\n          <span className=\"reqCount\">{tag}</span>\n        </div>\n      );\n\n      if ('req_list' in requirement) {\n        return (\n          <TreeView key={index} nodeLabel={reqLabel} itemClassName={finished}>\n            {this.populateReqTree(requirement)}\n          </TreeView>\n        );\n      } else {\n        return (\n          <TreeView key={index} itemClassName={finished} nodeLabel={reqLabel}>\n            {requirement['settled'] &&\n              requirement['settled'].map((course, index) => {\n                return (\n                  <li\n                    key={index}\n                    className=\"settled\"\n                    onClick={(e) => {\n                      this.toggleSettle(course, requirement['path_to'], false);\n                    }}\n                  >\n                    {course}\n                  </li>\n                );\n              })}\n            {requirement['unsettled'] &&\n              requirement['unsettled'].map((course, index) => {\n                return (\n                  <li\n                    key={index}\n                    className=\"unsettled text-muted\"\n                    onClick={(e) => {\n                      this.toggleSettle(course, requirement['path_to'], true);\n                    }}\n                  >\n                    {course}{' '}\n                    <i\n                      className=\"fa fa-exclamation-circle\"\n                      title=\"This course could satisfy multiple requirements. Click to settle it here.\"\n                    ></i>\n                  </li>\n                );\n              })}\n          </TreeView>\n        );\n      }\n    });\n  };\n\n  requirements = () => {\n    return this.props.requirements.map((mainReq, index) => {\n      let name;\n      let content;\n      let finished = '';\n      let popoverContent;\n\n      // major is supported\n      if (typeof mainReq === 'object') {\n        name = mainReq.name;\n        content = this.populateReqTree(mainReq);\n\n        // whether or not the major requirements have been satisfied\n        if (\n          (mainReq['min_needed'] === 0 && mainReq['count'] >= 0) ||\n          (mainReq['min_needed'] > 0 &&\n            mainReq['count'] >= mainReq['min_needed'])\n        ) {\n          finished = 'req-done';\n        }\n        // popover\n        popoverContent = '<div class=\"popoverContentContainer\">';\n        if (mainReq.explanation) {\n          popoverContent +=\n            '<p>' + mainReq.explanation.split('\\n').join('<br>') + '</p>';\n        } else if (mainReq.description) {\n          popoverContent +=\n            '<p>' + mainReq.description.split('\\n').join('<br>') + '</p>';\n        }\n        if (mainReq.contacts) {\n          popoverContent += '<h6>Contacts:</h6>';\n          mainReq.contacts.forEach((contact) => {\n            popoverContent +=\n              '<p>' +\n              contact.type +\n              ':<br>' +\n              contact.name +\n              '<br><a href=\"mailto:' +\n              contact.email +\n              '\">' +\n              contact.email +\n              '</a></p>';\n          });\n        }\n        if (mainReq.urls) {\n          popoverContent += '<h6>Reference Links:</h6>';\n          mainReq.urls.forEach((url) => {\n            popoverContent +=\n              '<p><a href=\"' +\n              url +\n              '\" class=\"ref-link\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">' +\n              url +\n              '</a></p>';\n          });\n        }\n        popoverContent += '</div>';\n      }\n      // major is not supported yet\n      else {\n        name = mainReq;\n        content = (\n          <div>\n            <p style={{ padding: '5px' }}>\n              The {name} major is not supported yet.     "/frontend/src/components/Schedule.js": "import React, { Component } from 'react';\nimport $ from 'jquery';\nimport Semester from 'components/Semester';\nimport styled from 'styled-components';\nimport { getSemesterNames } from 'utils/SemesterUtils';\nimport { addPopover } from 'Popover';\n\nconst Semesters = styled.div`\n  display: grid;\n  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, calc(25% - 3.75px));\n  grid-template-rows: repeat(2, 1fr);\n  height: inherit;\n  grid-gap: 5px;\n  padding: 0 5px;\n`;\n\nexport default class Schedule extends Component {\n  componentDidMount() {\n    if (this.props.schedule === null) {\n      // get existing schedule and populate semesters\n      $.ajax({\n        url: '/api/v1/get_schedule/',\n        datatype: 'json',\n        type: 'GET',\n        success: (schedule) => {\n          if (schedule) this.props.onChange('schedule', schedule);\n          this.addPopovers(schedule);\n        },\n      });\n    } else {\n      this.addPopovers(this.props.schedule);\n    }\n  }\n\n  componentDidUpdate(prevProps, prevState) {\n    if (this.props.schedule !== prevProps.schedule) {\n      this.addPopovers(this.props.schedule);\n    }\n  }\n\n  addPopovers = (schedule) => {\n    for (let semIndex = 0; semIndex < schedule.length; semIndex++) {\n      for (\n        let courseIndex = 0;\n        courseIndex < schedule[semIndex].length;\n        courseIndex++\n      ) {\n        let course = schedule[semIndex][courseIndex];\n        let courseKey = `course-card-${course['semester']}-${semIndex}-${courseIndex}`;\n        addPopover(course, courseKey, semIndex);\n      }\n    }\n  };\n\n  semesters = () => {\n    let profile = this.props.profile;\n    if (!profile || !profile.classYear) return [];\n\n    let semesterNames = getSemesterNames(profile.classYear);\n    let semesters = semesterNames.map((semName, index) => {\n      let semId = `sem${index}`;\n      return (\n        <Semester\n          key={semId}\n          onChange={this.props.onChange}\n          schedule={this.props.schedule}\n          semesterIndex={index}\n        >\n          {semName}\n        </Semester>\n      );\n    });\n    return semesters;\n  };\n\n  render() {\n    return <Semesters id=\"semesters\">{this.semesters()}</Semesters>;\n  }\n}",
    "/frontend/src/components/Search.js": "import React, { Component } from 'react';\nimport $ from 'jquery';\nimport SearchCard from 'components/SearchCard';\n\nexport default class Search extends       type: 'GET',\n        cache: true,\n        beforeSend: function () {\n          // if readyState is 4, then the request is already finished\n          if (\n            state.currentRequest !==     "/frontend/src/components/SearchCard.js": "import React, { Component } from 'react';\nimport SearchCourseCard from './SearchCourseCard';\n\nconst RADIX = 10;\nconst BASE_COURSE_OFFERINGS_URL = 'https://www.princetoncourses.com/course/';\n\nexport default class SearchCard extends Component {\n  /* Helper function to convert a semester into readable form */\n  convertSemToReadableForm = (sem) => {\n    if (sem[0] === 'f') {\n      return 'Fall 20' + sem.slice(1);\n    } else {\n      return 'Spring 20' + sem.slice(1);\n    }\n  };\n\n  /* Converts semester list to human readable form, using the two most recent semesters */\n  getPrevOfferedSemList = (semList) => {\n    // Sort semester list according to when they happened\n    semList.sort(function (sem1, sem2) {\n      let yearCmp =\n        parseInt(sem1.slice(1), RADIX) - parseInt(sem2.slice(1), RADIX);\n      if (yearCmp !== 0) return yearCmp;\n      else if (sem1[0] === 's' && sem2[0] === 'f') return -1;\n      else if (sem1[0] === 'f' && sem2[0] === 's') return 1;\n      else return 0;\n    });\n\n    // Convert to readable form\n    let result = '';\n    for (\n      let index = Math.max(0, semList.length - 2);\n      index < semList.length;\n      index++\n    ) {\n      result += this.convertSemToReadableForm(semList[index]);\n      if (index !== semList.length - 1) result += ', ';\n    }\n    return result;\n  };\n\n  /* Converts semester to term code */\n  convertSemToTermCode = (sem) => {\n    let code = '1';\n    if (sem[0] === 'f') {\n      code += (parseInt(sem.slice(1), 10) + 1).toString() + '2';\n    } else {\n      code += sem.slice(1) + '4';\n    }\n    return code;\n  };\n\n  render() {\n    let course = this.props.course;\n    let courseId = course['id'];\n    let courseSemList = course['semester_list'];\n    let termCode = this.convertSemToTermCode(\n      courseSemList[courseSemList.length - 1]\n    );\n\n    let courseInfoLink = `${BASE_COURSE_OFFERINGS_URL}${termCode}${courseId}`;\n    let prevOfferedSemList = this.getPrevOfferedSemList(courseSemList);\n\n    return (\n      <div className={`search-card ${course['semester']}`}>\n        <>\n          <SearchCourseCard\n            course={course}\n            courseKey={this.props.courseKey}\n            courseIndex={this.props.index}\n          />\n          <div className=\"search-card-info\">\n            <div>\n              <div className=\"course-title\">{course['title']}</div>\n              <div className=\"course-prev-sems\">{`Previously offered in ${prevOfferedSemList}`}</div>\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"search-card-links\">\n              <a\n                href={courseInfoLink}\n                target=\"_blank\"\n                rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\n              >\n                <i className=\"fas fa-info-circle fa-lg fa-fw course-info\" />\n              </a>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </>\n      </div>\n    );\n  }\n}",

    "/frontend/src/utils/SemesterUtils.js": "export const SEMESTER_TYPE = Object.freeze({\n  FALL_SEM: Symbol('fallSem'),\n  SPRING_SEM: Symbol('springSem'),\n  DEFAULT: Symbol('defaultSem'),\n});\n\nexport const DEFAULT_SCHEDULE = [[], [], [], [], [], [], [], [], []];\nexport const EXTERNAL_CREDITS_SEMESTER_INDEX = 8;\n\nexport function isFallSemester(semesterType) {\n  return semesterType === SEMESTER_TYPE.FALL_SEM;\n}\n\nexport function isSpringSemester(semesterType) {\n  return semesterType === SEMESTER_TYPE.SPRING_SEM;\n}\n\nexport function getSemesterType(semNum) {\n  if (semNum % 2 === 0 && semNum !== EXTERNAL_CREDITS_SEMESTER_INDEX) {\n    return SEMESTER_TYPE.FALL_SEM;\n  } else if (semNum % 2 === 1 && semNum !== EXTERNAL_CREDITS_SEMESTER_INDEX) {\n    return SEMESTER_TYPE.SPRING_SEM;\n  } else {\n    return SEMESTER_TYPE.DEFAULT;\n  }\n}\n\nexport function getSemesterNames(classYear) {\n  let semesterNames = [];\n  let year = classYear - 4;\n  let semesterType = SEMESTER_TYPE.FALL_SEM;\n\n  for (let i = 0; i < 8; i++) {\n    let semester = isFallSemester(semesterType) ? 'Fall' : 'Spring';\n\n    semesterNames.push(`${semester} ${year}`);\n\n    semesterType = isFallSemester(semesterType)\n      ? SEMESTER_TYPE.SPRING_SEM\n      : SEMESTER_TYPE.FALL_SEM;\n    if (isSpringSemester(semesterType)) year++;\n  }\n\n  return semesterNames;\n}\n\n/* Converts semester to term code */\nexport function convertSemToTermCode(sem) {\n  let code = '1';\n  if (sem[0] === 'f') {\n    code += (parseInt(sem.slice(1), 10) + 1).toString() + '2';\n  } else {\n    code += sem.slice(1) + '4';\n  }\n  return code;\n}",

    "/tigerpath/forms.py": "from django import forms\nfrom tigerpath.models import UserProfile, Major\nimport datetime\n\n\n# returns a list of tuples (year int, year string)\ndef create_year_choices():\n    # if the month is earlier than July, then show the seniors' class year; else, show the freshmen's class year\n    now = datetime.datetime.now()\n    offset = 0 if now.month < 7 else 1\n    return [(now.year + i, str(now.year + i)) for i in range(offset, offset + 4)]\n\n\n# returns a list of tuples (major code, major name)\ndef create_major_choices():\n    return Major.objects.order_by(\"name\").values_list(\"id\", \"name\")\n\n\nclass OnboardingForm(forms.ModelForm):\n    def __init__(self, *args, **kwargs):\n        super(OnboardingForm, self).__init__(*args, **kwargs)\n        self.fields[\"major\"].choices = create_major_choices()\n\n    class Meta:\n        # model and fields used for the form\n        model = UserProfile\n        fields = [\"nickname\", \"year\", \"major\"]\n        widgets = {\n            \"nickname\": forms.HiddenInput(),\n            \"year\": forms.Select(choices=create_year_choices()),\n        }\n\n\nclass SettingsForm(forms.ModelForm):\n    def __init__(self, *args, **kwargs):\n        super(SettingsForm, self).__init__(*args, **kwargs)\n        self.fields[\"major\"].choices = create_major_choices()\n\n    class Meta:\n        # model and fields used for the form\n        model = UserProfile\n        fields = [\"nickname\", \"year\", \"major\"]\n        widgets = {\"year\": forms.Select(choices=create_year_choices())}",
