    "/tigerpath/majors_and_certificates/scripts/verifier.py": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport yaml\nfrom pprint import pprint\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport collections\nimport time\nimport copy\nimport requests\n\nfrom . import university_info\n\nREMOTE_DATA_REPO_URL = (\n    \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TigerAppsOrg/Princeton-Departmental-Data/old/\"\n)\n\nMAJORS_LOCATION = (\n    \"majors/\"  # relative path to folder containing the major requirements JSONs\n)\nCERTIFICATES_LOCATION = \"certificates/\"  # relative path to folder containing the certificate requirements JSONs\nDEGREES_LOCATION = (\n    \"degrees/\"  # relative path to the folder containing the AB/BSE requirements JSONs\n)\n\nREQ_PATH_SEPARATOR = \"//\"\n# REQ_PATH_PREFIX := <type>//<year>//<dept_code or degree_code or certificate_name>\n# Limit the type to 12 characters and the code/name to 100 characters\nREQ_PATH_PREFIX = \"%.12s\" + REQ_PATH_SEPARATOR + \"%d\" + REQ_PATH_SEPARATOR + \"%.100s\"\n\nDEFAULT_SCHEDULE = [[]] * 8\n\n\ndef check_major(major_name, courses, year):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns information about the major requirements satisfied by the courses\n    given in courses.\n\n    :param major_name: the name of the major\n    :param courses: a list of course-listings\n    :param year: the user's class year for which to read the requirements\n    :type major_name: string\n    :type courses: 2D array\n    :type year: int\n    :returns: Whether the major requirements are satisfied\n    :returns: The list of courses with info about the requirements they satisfy\n    :returns: A simplified json with info about how much of each requirement is satisfied\n    :rtype: (bool, dict, dict)\n    \"\"\"\n    year = int(year)\n    if year < 2000 or year > 3000:\n        raise ValueError(\"Year is invalid.\")\n    if (\n        major_name not in university_info.AB_CONCENTRATIONS\n        and major_name not in university_info.BSE_CONCENTRATIONS\n    ):\n        raise ValueError(\"Major code not recognized.\")\n    major_filename = \"%s.yaml\" % major_name\n    major_filepath = os.path.join(MAJORS_LOCATION, major_filename)\n    return check_requirements(major_filepath, courses, year)\n\n\ndef check_degree(degree_name, courses, year):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns information about the degree requirements satisfied by the courses\n    given in courses.\n\n    :param degree_name: the name of the degree\n    :param courses: a list of course-listings\n    :param year: the user's class year for which to read the requirements\n    :type degree_name: string\n    :type courses: 2D array\n    :type year: int\n    :returns: Whether the degree requirements are satisfied\n    :returns: The list of courses with info about the requirements they satisfy\n    :returns: A simplified json with info about how much of each requirement is satisfied\n    :rtype: (bool, dict, dict)\n    \"\"\"\n    year = int(year)\n    degree_name = degree_name.upper()\n    if year < 2000 or year > 3000:\n        raise ValueError(\"Year is invalid.\")\n    if degree_name not in [\"AB\", \"BSE\"]:\n        raise ValueError(\"Invalid degree name: %s\" % degree_name)\n    degree_filename = \"%s.yaml\" % degree_name\n    degree_filepath = os.path.join(DEGREES_LOCATION, degree_filename)\n    return check_requirements(degree_filepath, courses, year)\n\n\ndef check_certificate(certificate_name, courses, year):\n    \"\"\"\n    NOTE: Not yet fully supported. Some certificate specific functionality may not\n    be present, or may break.\n\n    Returns information about the certificate requirements satisfied by the courses\n    given in courses.\n\n    :param certificate_name: the name of the certificate\n    :param courses: a list of course-listings\n    :param year: the user's class year for which to read the requirements\n    :type certificate_name: string\n    :type courses: 2D array\n    :type year: int\n    :returns: Whether the certificate requirements are satisfied\n    :returns: The list of courses with info about the requirements they satisfy\n    :returns: A simplified json with info about how much of each requirement is satisfied\n    :rtype: (bool, dict, dict)\n    \"\"\"\n    year = int(year)\n    if year < 2000 or year > 3000:\n        raise ValueError(\"Year is invalid.\")\n    if certificate_name not in university_info.CERTIFICATES:\n        raise ValueError(\"Certificate not recognized.\")\n    certificate_filename = \"%s.yaml\" % certificate_name\n    certificate_filepath = os.path.join(CERTIFICATES_LOCATION, certificate_filename)\n    return check_requirements(certificate_filepath, courses, year)\n\n\ndef check_requirements(req_file, courses, year):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns information about the requirements satisfied by the courses\n    given in courses.\n\n    :param req_file: the name of a file containing a requirements JSON\n    :param courses: a list of course-listings\n    :param year: the user's class year for which to read the requirements\n    :type req_file: string\n    :type courses: 2D array\n    :type year: int\n    :returns: Whether the requirements are satisfied\n    :returns: The list of courses with info about the requirements they satisfy\n    :returns: A simplified json with info about how much of each requirement is satisfied\n    :rtype: (bool, dict, dict)\n    \"\"\"\n    data = requests.get(REMOTE_DATA_REPO_URL + req_file).text\n    req = yaml.safe_load(data)\n    courses = _init_courses(courses, req, year)\n    req = _init_req(req, year)\n    _mark_possible_reqs(req, courses)\n    _assign_settled_courses_to_reqs(req, courses)\n    _add_course_lists_to_req(req, courses)\n    formatted_courses = _format_courses_output(courses)\n    formatted_req = _format_req_output(req)\n    return formatted_req[\"satisfied\"], formatted_courses, formatted_req\n\n\ndef get_courses_by_path(path):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns the sets of all courses and all distribution requirements\n    in the subtree specified by path as a tuple:\n    (course_set, dist_req_set)\n    Note: Sets may contain duplicate courses if a course is listed in multiple\n    different ways\n    Note: the path parameter must be a requirement path string that was generated\n    through calling _init_path_to()\n    Implementation is sensitive to the path format, which must start with\n    <type>//<year>//<dept_code>\n    where the <>'s are replaced with the appropriate values.\n\n    :param path: the path identifier of a requirement as generated by _init_path_to()\n    :type path: string\n    :raises: ValueError - if the path was not generated by _init_path_to()\n    :returns: the tuple (course_set, dist_req_set)\n    :rtype: (set, set)\n    \"\"\"\n    req_type, year, req_name = path.split(REQ_PATH_SEPARATOR)[:3]\n    year = int(year)\n    if year < 2000 or year > 3000:\n        raise ValueError(\"Path malformatted.\")\n    if not path.startswith(REQ_PATH_PREFIX % (req_type, year, req_name)):\n        raise ValueError(\"Path malformatted.\")\n    if \"/\" in req_type or \"/\" in req_name:\n        raise ValueError(\"Path malformatted.\")\n    filename = \"%s.yaml\" % req_name\n    if req_type == \"Major\":\n        if (\n            req_name not in university_info.AB_CONCENTRATIONS\n            and req_name not in university_info.BSE_CONCENTRATIONS\n        ):\n            raise ValueError(\"Path malformatted.\")\n        req_filepath = os.path.join(MAJORS_LOCATION, filename)\n    elif req_type == \"Certificate\":\n        if req_name not in university_info.CERTIFICATES:\n            raise ValueError(\"Path malformatted.\")\n        req_filepath = os.path.join(CERTIFICATES_LOCATION, filename)\n    elif req_type == \"Degree\":\n        if req_name not in [\"AB\", \"BSE\"]:\n            raise ValueError(\"Path malformatted.\")\n        req_filepath = os.path.join(DEGREES_LOCATION, filename)\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(\"Path malformatted.\")\n    data = requests.get(REMOTE_DATA_REPO_URL + req_filepath).text\n    req = yaml.safe_load(data)\n    _init_year_switch(req, year)\n    subreq = _get_req_by_path(req, path, year)\n    if not subreq:\n        raise ValueError(\"Path malformatted: \" + path)\n    return _get_collapsed_course_and_dist_req_sets(subreq)\n\n\ndef _init_req(req, year):\n    req = copy.deepcopy(req)\n    _init_year_switch(req, year)\n    _init_req_fields(req)\n    _init_min_ALL(req)\n    _init_double_counting_allowed(req)\n    _init_path_to(req, year)\n    return req\n\n\ndef _format_req_output(req):\n    \"\"\"\n    Enforce the type and order of fields in the req output\n    \"\"\"\n    output = collections.OrderedDict()\n    if req[\"name\"] == None:  # hidden requirement. Do not show.\n        return None\n    for key in [\"name\", \"code\", \"degree\", \"path_to\", \"urls\"]:\n        if key in req:\n            output[key] = req[key]\n    if \"code\" in req and \"description\" in req:\n        output[\"description\"] = req[\"description\"]\n    if \"contacts\" in req:\n        output[\"contacts\"] = []\n        for contact in req[\"contacts\"]:\n            contact_copy = collections.OrderedDict()\n            for key in [\"type\", \"name\", \"email\"]:\n                contact_copy[key] = contact[key]\n            output[\"contacts\"].append(contact_copy)\n    for key in [\"explanation\", \"pdfs_allowed\", \"completed_by_semester\"]:\n        if key in req:\n            output[key] = req[key]\n    output[\"satisfied\"] = req[\"min_needed\"] - req[\"count\"] <= 0\n    for key in [\"count\", \"min_needed\", \"max_counted\"]:\n        output[key] = req[key]\n    if \"req_list\" in req:  # internal node. recursively call on children\n        req_list = []\n        for subreq in req[\"req_list\"]:\n            child = _format_req_output(subreq)\n            if child != None:\n                req_list.append(_format_req_output(subreq))\n        if req_list:\n            output[\"req_list\"] = req_list\n    if \"settled\" in req:\n        output[\"settled\"] = req[\"settled\"]\n    if \"unsettled\" in req:\n        output[\"unsettled\"] = req[\"unsettled\"]\n    return output\n\n\ndef _add_course_lists_to_req(req, courses):\n    \"\"\"\n    Add course lists for each requirement that either\n    (a) has no subrequirements, or\n    (b) has hidden subrequirements\n    \"\"\"\n    include_course_lists = False\n    if \"req_list\" in req:\n        for subreq in req[\"req_list\"]:\n            if subreq[\"name\"] == None:\n                include_course_lists = True\n            else:  # recursively for all named requirements\n                _add_course_lists_to_req(subreq, courses)\n    else:\n        include_course_lists = True\n    if include_course_lists:\n        req[\"settled\"] = []\n        req[\"unsettled\"] = []\n        for sem in courses:\n            for course in sem:\n                if req[\"double_counting_allowed\"]:\n                    if len(course[\"reqs_double_counted\"]) > 0:\n                        for path in course[\"reqs_double_counted\"]:\n                            if path.startswith(req[\"path_to\"]):\n                                req[\"settled\"].append(course[\"name\"])\n                                ## add to reqs_satisfied because couldn't be added in _assign_settled_courses_to_reqs()\n                                course[\"reqs_satisfied\"].append(req[\"path_to\"])\n                elif len(course[\"settled\"]) > 0:\n                    for path in course[\"settled\"]:\n                        if path.startswith(req[\"path_to\"]):\n                            req[\"settled\"].append(course[\"name\"])\n                else:\n                    for path in course[\"possible_reqs\"]:\n                        if path.startswith(req[\"path_to\"]):\n                            req[\"unsettled\"].append(course[\"name\"])\n                            break\n\n\ndef _init_courses(courses, req, year):\n    if not courses:\n        courses = DEFAULT_SCHEDULE\n    else:\n        courses = copy.deepcopy(courses)\n    for sem_num, semester in enumerate(courses):\n        for course in semester:\n            course[\"name\"] = _get_course_name_from_pattern(course[\"name\"])\n            course[\"possible_reqs\"] = []\n            course[\"reqs_satisfied\"] = []\n            course[\n                \"reqs_double_counted\"\n            ] = []  # reqs satisfied for which double counting allowed\n            course[\"semester_number\"] = sem_num\n            course[\n                \"num_settleable\"\n            ] = 0  # number of reqs to which can be settled. autosettled if 1\n            if \"external\" not in course:\n                course[\"external\"] = False\n            if \"settled\" not in course or course[\"settled\"] == None:\n                course[\"settled\"] = []\n            elif req[\"type\"] in [\n                \"Major\",\n                \"Degree\",\n            ]:  # filter out irrelevant requirements from list\n                for path in course[\"settled\"]:\n                    if not path.startswith(\n                        REQ_PATH_PREFIX % (req[\"type\"], year, req[\"code\"])\n                    ):\n                        course[\"settled\"].remove(path)\n            else:  # type must be \"Certificate\"\n                for path in course[\"settled\"]:\n                    if not path.startswith(\n                        REQ_PATH_PREFIX % (req[\"type\"], year, req[\"name\"])\n                    ):\n                        course[\"settled\"].remove(path)\n    return courses\n\n\ndef _format_courses_output(courses):\n    \"\"\"\n    Enforce the type and order of fields in the courses output\n    \"\"\"\n    output = []\n    for i, sem in enumerate(courses):\n        output.append([])\n        for j, course in enumerate(sem):\n            output[i].append(collections.OrderedDict())\n            for key in [\"name\", \"possible_reqs\", \"reqs_satisfied\"]:\n                output[i][j][key] = course[key]\n            if len(course[\"settled\"]) > 0:  # only show if non-empty\n                output[i][j][\"settled\"] = course[\"settled\"]\n    return output\n\n\ndef _year_matches_code(year, code):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns whether `year` falls in the range specified by `code`\n    \"\"\"\n    if isinstance(code, int):  # explicitly specified year as an int\n        return year == code\n    if not code or code.lower() == \"default\":  # empty indicates default case\n        return True\n    code = code.replace(\" \", \"\")  # strip it of spaces for processing\n    if code.startswith(\"<=\"):\n        return year <= int(code[2:])\n    elif code.startswith(\">=\"):\n        return year >= int(code[2:])\n    elif code.startswith(\"<\"):\n        return year < int(code[1:])\n    elif code.startswith(\">\"):\n        return year > int(code[1:])\n    elif code.startswith(\"==\"):\n        return year == int(code[2:])\n    elif code.startswith(\"!=\"):\n        return year != int(code[2:])\n    elif \"-\" in code:  # range of years (inclusive), such as \"2018-2020\"\n        fr, to, *_ = code.split(\"-\")\n        return year >= int(fr) and year <= int(to)\n    else:  # just the year is the same as ==\n        return year == int(code)\n\n\ndef _init_year_switch(req, year):\n    \"\"\"\n    Checks for any year_switch primitives and selects the right subrequirements.\n\n    Any requirement that contains a year_switch is overridden by the first\n    subrequirement of that year_switch whose year code matches the user's\n    class year.\n    Fields in req are overridden by any explicitly listed fields of the\n    overriding subrequirement, but any fields not specified by the\n    subrequirement remain as is (except the year_switch, which is removed).\n\n    If no year code matches, the requirement is unchanged and the year_switch\n    is just removed (that is, the year_switch is ignored and has no effect).\n    \"\"\"\n    if \"year_switch\" in req:\n        newreq = {}\n        for subreq in req[\"year_switch\"]:\n            code = subreq.get(\"year_code\", None)  # year_code set to default\n            if _year_matches_code(year, code):\n                newreq = subreq\n                break  # stop at the first year code that matches\n        del req[\"year_switch\"]\n        if \"year_code\" in newreq:\n            del newreq[\"year_code\"]\n        req.update(newreq)  # override with the values from subreq\n    # Note that the recursive case below can always still happen even if the\n    # year_switch above was triggered, since it may have just gained a req_list\n    # from the overriding subrequirement.\n    if \"req_list\" in req:\n        for subreq in req[\"req_list\"]:\n            _init_year_switch(subreq, year)\n\n\ndef _init_req_fields(req):\n    \"\"\"\n    Initializes all the counts to zero and ensures that min_needed and\n    max_counted exist.\n    \"\"\"\n    req[\"count\"] = 0\n    if (\"name\" not in req) or (req[\"name\"] == \"\") or (req[\"name\"] == None):\n        req[\"name\"] = None\n    if \"no_req\" in req:  # enforce that no_req cannot require a non-zero count\n        req[\"no_req\"] = None  # ignore the contents of a no_req\n        req[\"min_needed\"] = 0\n        req[\"max_counted\"] = 0\n    if \"min_needed\" not in req or req[\"min_needed\"] == None:\n        if \"type\" in req:  # check for root\n            req[\"min_needed\"] = \"ALL\"\n        else:\n            req[\"min_needed\"] = 0\n    if \"max_counted\" not in req:\n        req[\"max_counted\"] = None\n    if \"req_list\" in req:\n        for subreq in req[\"req_list\"]:\n            _init_req_fields(subreq)\n    elif \"course_list\" in req and \"excluded_course_list\" not in req:\n        req[\"excluded_course_list\"] = []\n    elif \"num_courses\" in req:\n        req[\"min_needed\"] = req[\"num_courses\"]\n    if \"dist_req\" in req and isinstance(req[\"dist_req\"], str):\n        req[\"dist_req\"] = [\n            req[\"dist_req\"]\n        ]  # backwards compatibility with non-list dist_req\n    return req\n\n\ndef _init_min_ALL(req):\n    \"\"\"\n    Replaces every instance of min_needed=\"ALL\" with the actual number.\n    \"\"\"\n    num_counted_from_below = 0\n    if \"req_list\" in req:\n        for subreq in req[\"req_list\"]:\n            num_counted_from_below += _init_min_ALL(subreq)\n    elif \"course_list\" in req:  # written as loop in case other actions neeed later\n        for _ in req[\"course_list\"]:\n            num_counted_from_below += 1\n    elif \"dist_req\" in req or \"num_courses\" in req:\n        if req[\"max_counted\"]:\n            num_counted_from_below += req[\"max_counted\"]\n    if req[\"min_needed\"] == \"ALL\":\n        req[\"min_needed\"] = num_counted_from_below\n    if req[\"max_counted\"] == None:\n        return num_counted_from_below\n    else:\n        return min(req[\"max_counted\"], num_counted_from_below)\n\n\ndef _init_double_counting_allowed(req, from_parent=False):\n    \"\"\"\n    Initializes the double_counting_allowed field in all subtrees\n    \"\"\"\n    if \"double_counting_allowed\" not in req:\n        req[\"double_counting_allowed\"] = from_parent\n    if \"req_list\" in req:\n        for subreq in req[\"req_list\"]:\n            _init_double_counting_allowed(subreq, req[\"double_counting_allowed\"])\n\n\ndef _init_path_to(req, year):\n    \"\"\"\n    Assign a path identifier to each node/subrequirement in the requirements\n    tree with the properties:\n    1. The path is unique (no two nodes in the tree have the same path) as long\n        as no two subrequirements in the same subtree have the same name.\n    2. The path gives the traversal of the tree needed to reach that node.\n    \"\"\"\n    if \"path_to\" not in req:  # only for root of the tree\n        if req[\"type\"] in [\"Major\", \"Degree\"]:\n            req[\"path_to\"] = REQ_PATH_PREFIX % (req[\"type\"], year, req[\"code\"])\n        else:  # type must be \"Certificate\"\n            req[\"path_to\"] = REQ_PATH_PREFIX % (req[\"type\"], year, req[\"name\"])\n    if \"req_list\" in req:\n        for i, subreq in enumerate(req[\"req_list\"]):\n            # the identifier is the req name if present, or otherwise, an identifying number\n            identifier = \"\"\n            if (\n                (\"name\" not in subreq)\n                or (subreq[\"name\"] == \"\")\n                or (subreq[\"name\"] == None)\n            ):\n                identifier = \"%03d\" % i\n            else:\n                identifier = subreq[\"name\"]\n            subreq[\"path_to\"] = req[\"path_to\"] + REQ_PATH_SEPARATOR + str(identifier)\n            _init_path_to(subreq, year)\n\n\ndef _json_format(obj):\n    import json\n\n    return json.dumps(obj, sort_keys=False, indent=2, separators=(\",\", \": \")) + \"\\n\"\n\n\ndef _get_dir_path():\n    return os.path.dirname(os.path.realpath(__file__))\n\n\ndef _mark_possible_reqs(req, courses):\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds all the requirements that each course can satisfy.\n    \"\"\"\n    if \"req_list\" in req:  # recursively check subrequirements\n        for subreq in req[\"req_list\"]:\n            _mark_possible_reqs(subreq, courses)\n    else:  # note: course_list and dist_req can both be specified for the same req\n        if \"course_list\" in req:\n            _mark_courses(req, courses)\n        if \"dist_req\" in req:\n            _mark_dist(req, courses)\n\n\ndef _assign_settled_courses_to_reqs(req, courses):\n    \"\"\"\n    Assigns only settled courses and those that can only satify one requirement,\n    and updates the appropriate counts.\n    \"\"\"\n    old_deficit = req[\"min_needed\"] - req[\"count\"]\n    if req[\"max_counted\"] != None:\n        old_available = req[\"max_counted\"] - req[\"count\"]\n    was_satisfied = old_deficit <= 0\n    newly_satisfied = 0\n    if \"req_list\" in req:  # recursively check subrequirements\n        for subreq in req[\"req_list\"]:\n            newly_satisfied += _assign_settled_courses_to_reqs(subreq, courses)\n    elif req[\"double_counting_allowed\"]:\n        newly_satisfied = _mark_all(req, courses)\n    elif \"course_list\" in req:\n        newly_satisfied = _mark_settled(req, courses)\n    elif \"dist_req\" in req:\n        newly_satisfied = _mark_settled(req, courses)\n    elif \"num_courses\" in req:\n        newly_satisfied = _check_degree_progress(req, courses)\n    req[\"count\"] += newly_satisfied\n    new_deficit = req[\"min_needed\"] - req[\"count\"]\n    if (not was_satisfied) and (new_deficit <= 0):  # this req just became satisfied\n        if req[\"max_counted\"] == None:  # unlimited\n            return req[\"count\"]\n        else:\n            return min(req[\"max_counted\"], req[\"count\"])  # cut off at max\n    elif (was_satisfied) and (\n        new_deficit <= 0\n    ):  # this requirement was already satisfied, but added more\n        if req[\"max_counted\"] == None:  # unlimited\n            return newly_satisfied\n        else:\n            return min(old_available, newly_satisfied)  # cut off at old_available\n    else:  # requirement still not satisfied\n        return 0\n\n\ndef _mark_courses(req, courses):\n    num_marked = 0\n    for sem in courses:\n        for c in sem:\n            if req[\"path_to\"] in c[\"possible_reqs\"]:  # already used\n                continue\n            excluded = False\n            for pattern in req[\"excluded_course_list\"]:\n                if _course_match(c[\"name\"], pattern):\n                    excluded = True\n            if excluded:  # this course cannot count for this req, so skip it\n                continue\n            for pattern in req[\"course_list\"]:\n                if _course_match(c[\"name\"], pattern):\n                    num_marked += 1\n                    c[\"possible_reqs\"].append(req[\"path_to\"])\n                    if not req[\"double_counting_allowed\"]:\n                        c[\"num_settleable\"] += 1\n                    break\n    return num_marked\n\n\ndef _mark_dist(req, courses):\n    num_marked = 0\n    for sem in courses:\n        for c in sem:\n            if req[\"path_to\"] in c[\"possible_reqs\"]:  # already used\n                continue\n            if c[\"dist_area\"] is None:\n                continue\n            dist_areas = c[\"dist_area\"].split(\",\")\n            if bool(set(dist_areas) & set(req[\"dist_req\"])):\n                num_marked += 1\n                c[\"possible_reqs\"].append(req[\"path_to\"])\n                if not req[\"double_counting_allowed\"]:\n                    c[\"num_settleable\"] += 1\n    return num_marked\n\n\ndef _mark_settled(req, courses):\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds and marks all courses in 'courses' that have been settled to\n    this requirement.\n    \"\"\"\n    num_marked = 0\n    for sem in courses:\n        for c in sem:\n            if len(c[\"reqs_satisfied\"]) > 0:  # already used in some subreq\n                continue\n            if len(c[\"settled\"]) > 0:\n                for p in c[\"settled\"]:  # go through the settled paths\n                    if p in req[\"path_to\"] and (\n                        c[\"external\"] or req[\"path_to\"] in c[\"possible_reqs\"]\n                    ):  # c was settled into this requirement\n                        num_marked += 1\n                        c[\"reqs_satisfied\"].append(req[\"path_to\"])\n                        break\n            elif c[\"num_settleable\"] == 1 and req[\"path_to\"] in c[\"possible_reqs\"]:\n                num_marked += 1\n                c[\"reqs_satisfied\"].append(req[\"path_to\"])\n                c[\"settled\"].append(req[\"path_to\"])\n    return num_marked\n\n\ndef _mark_all(req, courses):\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds and marks all courses in 'courses' that satisfy a requirement where\n    double counting is allowed.\n    \"\"\"\n    num_marked = 0\n    for sem in courses:\n        for c in sem:\n            if req[\"path_to\"] in c[\"possible_reqs\"]:\n                num_marked += 1\n                c[\"reqs_double_counted\"].append(req[\"path_to\"])\n            elif c[\"external\"]:\n                for p in c[\"settled\"]:\n                    if p in req[\"path_to\"]:\n                        num_marked += 1\n                        c[\"reqs_satisfied\"].append(req[\"path_to\"])\n    return num_marked\n\n\ndef _check_degree_progress(req, courses):\n    \"\"\"\n    Checks whether the correct number of courses have been completed by the\n    end of semester number 'by_semester' (1-8)\n    \"\"\"\n    by_semester = req[\"completed_by_semester\"]\n    num_courses = 0\n    if by_semester == None or by_semester > len(courses):\n        by_semester = len(courses)\n    for i in range(by_semester):\n        num_courses += len(courses[i])\n    return num_courses\n\n\ndef _course_match(course_name, pattern):\n    pattern = _get_course_name_from_pattern(pattern)\n    pattern = [\n        \"\".join(p.split()).upper() for p in pattern.split(\"/\")\n    ]  # split by '/' and\n    course = [\n        \"\".join(c.split()).upper() for c in course_name.split(\"/\")\n    ]  # remove spaces\n    for c in course:\n        for p in pattern:\n            if c == p:  # exact name matched\n                return True\n            if (\n                p[:4] == \"LANG\" and c[:3] in university_info.LANG_DEPTS\n            ):  # language course\n                if c[3:] == p[4:]:  # course numbers match\n                    return True\n                if len(p) > 4 and p[4] == \"*\":  # 'LANG*' or 'LANG***'\n                    return True\n                if (\n                    len(c) >= 4 and len(p) > 5 and p[5] == \"*\" and c[3:4] == p[4:5]\n                ):  # 'LANG1*' or 'LANG1**'\n                    return True\n                if (\n                    len(c) >= 5 and len(p) > 6 and p[6] == \"*\" and c[3:5] == p[4:6]\n                ):  # 'LANG12*'\n                    return True\n                if (\n                    len(c) >= 6 and len(p) > 7 and p[7] == \"*\" and c[3:6] == p[4:7]\n                ):  # 'LANG123*'\n                    return True\n            # non-language course\n            if (\n                len(c) >= 3 and len(p) > 3 and p[3] == \"*\" and c[:3] == p[:3]\n            ):  # 'AAA*' or 'AAA***'\n                return True\n            if (\n                len(c) >= 4 and len(p) > 4 and p[4] == \"*\" and c[:4] == p[:4]\n            ):  # 'AAA1*' or 'AAA1**'\n                return True\n            if (\n                len(c) >= 5 and len(p) > 5 and p[5] == \"*\" and c[:5] == p[:5]\n            ):  # 'AAA12*'  Note: not currently in format spec\n                return True\n            if (\n                len(c) >= 6 and len(p) > 6 and p[6] == \"*\" and c[:6] == p[:6]\n            ):  # 'AAA123*' matches to 'AAA123C'\n                return True\n    return False\n\n\ndef _get_req_by_path(req, path_to, year):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns the subrequirement of req that is pointed to by path_to\n    \"\"\"\n    if \"path_to\" not in req:\n        _init_path_to(req, year)\n    if req[\"path_to\"] == path_to:\n        return req\n    if \"req_list\" in req:\n        for subreq in req[\"req_list\"]:\n            result = _get_req_by_path(subreq, path_to, year)\n            if result:\n                return result\n    return None\n\n\ndef _get_collapsed_course_and_dist_req_sets(req):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns the sets of all courses and all distribution requirements\n    in req's subtree as a tuple:\n    (course_set, dist_req_set)\n    Note: Sets may contain duplicate courses if a course is listed in multiple\n    different ways\n    \"\"\"\n    if \"course_list\" in req or \"dist_req\" in req:\n        course_set = set()\n        dist_req_set = set()\n        if \"course_list\" in req:\n            for course in req[\"course_list\"]:\n                course = _get_course_name_from_pattern(course)\n                course_set.add(course)\n        if \"dist_req\" in req:\n            dist = req[\"dist_req\"]\n            if isinstance(dist, str):  # backwards compatibility with non-list dist_req\n                dist = [dist]\n            dist_req_set.update(dist)\n        return (course_set, dist_req_set)\n    total_course_set = set()\n    total_dist_req_set = set()\n    if \"req_list\" in req:\n        for subreq in req[\"req_list\"]:\n            course_set, dist_req_set = _get_collapsed_course_and_dist_req_sets(subreq)\n            if course_set:\n                total_course_set |= course_set  # union of both sets\n            if dist_req_set:\n                total_dist_req_set |= dist_req_set  # union of both sets\n    return (total_course_set, total_dist_req_set)\n\n\ndef _get_course_name_from_pattern(pattern):\n    if type(pattern) == dict:\n        return list(pattern.keys())[0]\n\n    return pattern.split(\":\")[0]  # remove course title\n\n\ndef main():\n    with open(\"verifier_tests/1.test\", \"r\", encoding=\"utf8\") as f:\n        major_name = f.readline()[:-1]\n        year = int(f.readline())\n        courses = yaml.safe_load(f)\n    satisfied, courses, major = check_major(major_name, courses, year)\n    print(_json_format(courses))\n    print(_json_format(major))\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()",
    "/tigerpath/majors_and_certificates/scripts/verifier_tester.py": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport json\nimport yaml\nfrom pprint import pprint\nimport jsonschema  # must be installed via pip\nimport os\nimport collections\nimport filecmp\nimport shutil\n\nfrom . import verifier\n\nDIR_PATH = os.path.dirname(\n    os.path.realpath(__file__)\n)  # the directory containing this file\nSCHEMA_LOCATION = os.path.join(\n    DIR_PATH, \"schema.json\"\n)  # path to the requirements JSON schema\nTESTS_LOCATION = os.path.join(\n    DIR_PATH, \"verifier_tests\"\n)  # folder where the test files are stored\n\n\ndef _json_format(obj):\n    return json.dumps(obj, sort_keys=False, indent=2, separators=(\",\", \": \")) + \"\\n\"\n\n\ndef main():\n    test_failed = None\n    for filename in sorted(os.listdir(TESTS_LOCATION)):\n        if filename.endswith(\".test\"):\n            print(\"Testing: \" + filename)\n            file_path = os.path.join(TESTS_LOCATION, filename)\n            with open(file_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf8\") as f:\n                req_name = f.readline()[:-1]\n                year = int(f.readline())\n                courses = yaml.safe_load(f)\n            if req_name in [\n                \"AB\",\n                \"BSE\",\n            ]:  # checking degree. No validation for degree jsons\n                satisfied, courses, req_tree = verifier.check_degree(\n                    req_name, courses, year\n                )\n            elif \"Certificate:\" in req_name:\n                req_name = \"\".join(req_name.split(\"Certificate:\")[1:])\n                major_filename = req_name + \"_\" + str(year) + \".json\"\n                major_filepath = os.path.join(\n                    DIR_PATH, verifier.CERTIFICATES_LOCATION, major_filename\n                )\n                with open(major_filepath, \"r\", encoding=\"utf8\") as f:\n                    requirements = yaml.safe_load(f)\n                with open(SCHEMA_LOCATION, \"r\", encoding=\"utf8\") as s:\n                    schema = yaml.safe_load(s)\n                jsonschema.validate(requirements, schema)\n                satisfied, courses, req_tree = verifier.check_certificate(\n                    req_name, courses, year\n                )\n            else:  # checking major\n                major_filename = req_name + \"_\" + str(year) + \".json\"\n                major_filepath = os.path.join(\n                    DIR_PATH, verifier.MAJORS_LOCATION, major_filename\n                )\n                with open(major_filepath, \"r\", encoding=\"utf8\") as f:\n                    requirements = yaml.safe_load(f)\n                with open(SCHEMA_LOCATION, \"r\", encoding=\"utf8\") as s:\n                    schema = yaml.safe_load(s)\n                jsonschema.validate(requirements, schema)\n                satisfied, courses, req_tree = verifier.check_major(\n                    req_name, courses, year\n                )\n            with open(file_path + \".out\", \"w\", encoding=\"utf8\") as f:\n                f.write(_json_format(courses))\n                f.write(\"\\n\")\n                f.write(_json_format(req_tree))\n            # use the most informative diff output\n            if shutil.which(\"colordiff\"):\n                diff = \"colordiff\"\n            elif shutil.which(\"diff\"):\n                diff = \"diff\"\n            else:\n                diff = \"cmp\"\n            # check if output is correct\n            if not filecmp.cmp(file_path + \".expected\", file_path + \".out\"):\n                print(\"--- Failed\")\n                if test_failed == None:\n                    test_failed = \"echo 'Failed test:' %s; %s %s %s | head -10\" % (\n                        file_path,\n                        diff,\n                        file_path + \".expected\",\n                        file_path + \".out\",\n                    )\n    if test_failed:\n        os.system(test_failed)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()",

The advanced science and core chemical engineering courses in the sophomore and junior years provide the fundamental tools of thermodynamics, transport processes, and reactor analysis. In the spring semester of the junior year, students take a laboratory-based course that utilizes core chemical engineering knowledge. In the senior year, students undertake an in-depth design analysis with state-of-the-art design and optimization tools. Students can tailor their specific interests in chemical and biological engineering by pursuing an area of concentration that culminates with a senior thesis project. The areas of concentration, reflective of the practice of modern chemical engineering, include bioengineering and biotechnology; materials and product engineering; energy and environmental engineering; optimization, dynamics, and information technology; entrepreneurship and management; and science and engineering for new technologies. student must satisfy the requirements of the School of Engineering and Applied Science and must choose courses during the sophomore, junior, and senior years to provide a core knowledge of chemical engineering and advanced knowledge in an area of concentration. The advanced science and core chemical engineering courses in the sophomore and junior years provide the fundamental tools of thermodynamics, transport processes, and reactor analysis. In the spring semester of the junior year, students take a laboratory-based course that utilizes core chemical engineering knowledge. In the senior year, students undertake an in-depth design analysis with state-of-the-art design and optimization tools. Students can tailor their specific interests in chemical and biological engineering by pursuing an area of concentration that culminates with a senior thesis project. The areas of concentration, reflective of the practice of modern chemical engineering, include bioengineering and biotechnology; materials and product engineering; energy and environmental engineering; optimization, dynamics, and information technology; entrepreneurship and management; and science and engineering for new technologies. The chemical engineering program is accredited by the Engineering Accreditation Commission of ABET, http://www.abet.org (link is external). Students with special interests should consult the section on special programs and options. student must satisfy the requirements of the School of Engineering and Applied Science and must choose courses during the sophomore, junior, and senior years to provide a core knowledge of chemical engineering and advanced knowledge in an area of concentration. The advanced science and core chemical engineering courses in the sophomore and junior years provide the fundamental tools of thermodynamics, transport processes, and reactor analysis. In the spring semester of the junior year, students take a laboratory-based course that utilizes core chemical engineering knowledge. In the senior year, students undertake an in-depth design analysis with state-of-the-art design and optimization tools. Students can tailor their specific interests in chemical and biological engineering by pursuing an area of concentration that culminates with a senior thesis project. The areas of concentration, reflective of the practice of modern chemical engineering, include bioengineering and biotechnology; materials and product engineering; energy and environmental engineering; optimization, dynamics, and information technology; entrepreneurship and management; and science and engineering for new technologies. The chemical engineering program is accredited by the Engineering Accreditation Commission of ABET, http://www.abet.org (link is external). Students with special interests should consult the section on special programs and options. A junior project normally involves the study and solution of specific problems, often associated with a research project. It may require a significant programming effort, a theoretical study involving the design and analysis of algorithms, or an applications problem in some other field. The results of these efforts must be presented in two written reports and posters that correspond to the work undertaken in each of the terms. The senior thesis may be a study in greater depth of one of the subjects considered in junior independent work, or it may deal with another aspect of computer science and its application.\\n\\nIndependent work is one of the unique features of a Princeton education. Independent projects typically arise either from an idea that excites you or from an idea put forth by a professor in the department. The department maintains a wiki of faculty research interests. This list is a good place to start in looking for a project or advisor. There is also some general advice on finding a topic, an adviser, and a successful outcome here.\\n\\nOnce you have a project, get a form (located on the bulletin board outside the Computer Science undergraduate office) and sign it along with your advisor to let us know what you'll be doing. Your project is then between you and your advisor, but there is always a COS Independent Work Coordinator who coordinates all independent work, and schedules public talks, checkpoints, and other requirements.\\n\\nIt is possible to do a project with a faculty member in another department if you have the approval of the Independent Work Coordinator.\",\n      \"satisfied\": true,\n      \"count\": 0,\n      \"min_needed\": 0,\n      \"max_counted\": null,\n      \"settled\": [],\n      \"unsettled\": []\n    }\n  ]\n}",

A junior project normally involves the study and solution of specific problems, often associated with a research project. It may require a significant programming effort, a theoretical study involving the design and analysis of algorithms, or an applications problem in some other field. The results of these efforts must be presented in two written reports and posters that correspond to the work undertaken in each of the terms. The senior thesis may be a study in greater depth of one of the subjects considered in junior independent work, or it may deal with another aspect of computer science and its application.\\n\\nIndependent work is one of the unique features of a Princeton education. Independent projects typically arise either from an idea that excites you or from an idea put forth by a professor in the department. The department maintains a wiki of faculty research interests. This list is a good place to start in looking for a project or advisor. There is also some general advice on finding a topic, an adviser, and a successful outcome here.\\n\\nOnce you have a project, get a form (located on the bulletin board outside the Computer Science undergraduate office) and sign it along with your advisor to let us know what you'll be doing. Your project is then between you and your advisor, but there is always a COS Independent Work Coordinator who coordinates all independent work, and schedules public talks, checkpoints, and other requirements.\\n\\nIt is possible to do a project with a faculty member in another department if you have the approval of the Independent Work Coordinator.\",\n      \"satisfied\": true,\n      \"count\": 0,\n      \"min_needed\": 0,\n      \"max_counted\": null,\n      \"settled\": [],\n      \"unsettled\": []\n    }\n  ]\n}",

A junior project normally involves the study and solution of specific problems, often associated with a research project. It may require a significant programming effort, a theoretical study involving the design and analysis of algorithms, or an applications problem in some other field. The results of these efforts must be presented in two written reports and posters that correspond to the work undertaken in each of the terms. The senior thesis may be a study in greater depth of one of the subjects considered in junior independent work, or it may deal with another aspect of computer science and its application.\\n\\nIndependent work is one of the unique features of a Princeton education. Independent projects typically arise either from an idea that excites you or from an idea put forth by a professor in the department. The department maintains a wiki of faculty research interests.     "/tigerpath/models.py": "from django.db import models\nfrom django.db.models.signals import post_save\nfrom django.dispatch import receiver\nfrom django.conf import settings\nfrom django.contrib.auth.models import User\nfrom django.contrib.postgres.fields import JSONField, ArrayField\nfrom django.contrib import admin\n\nimport uuid\n\n\nclass Semester(models.Model):\n    # fields\n    start_date = models.DateField()\n    end_date = models.DateField()\n    \"\"\" term_code = 1xxy, where xx is the year in which the school year ends,\n    and y is the semester code. y = 2 for the fall term, y = 4 for the spring\n    Example:\n    1144 = 1314Spring\n    1132 = 1213Fall\n    \"\"\"\n    term_code = models.CharField(\n        max_length=4, default=max(settings.ACTIVE_TERMS), db_index=True, unique=True\n    )\n\n    def __unicode__(self):\n        end_year = int(self.term_code[1:3])\n        start_year = end_year - 1\n        if int(self.term_code[3]) == 2:\n            sem = \"Fall\"\n        else:\n            sem = \"Spring\"\n        return str(start_year) + \"-\" + str(end_year) + \" \" + sem\n\n\nclass Professor(models.Model):\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=100)\n\n\nclass Course(models.Model):\n    # relationships\n    semester = models.ForeignKey(Semester, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    professors = models.ManyToManyField(Professor)\n\n    # fields\n    title = models.TextField()\n    rating = models.FloatField(default=0)\n    description = models.TextField()\n    registrar_id = models.CharField(max_length=20)\n    dist_area = models.TextField(default=\"\")\n    all_semesters = ArrayField(\n        models.CharField(max_length=4),\n        default=list,\n        blank=True,\n    )\n    is_master = models.BooleanField(default=False)\n    cross_listings = models.TextField(default=\"\")\n\n    def course_listings(self):\n        # + ' ' + ': ' + self.title\n        return \" / \".join(\n            [\n                unicode(course_listing)\n                for course_listing in self.course_listing_set.all().order_by(\"dept\")\n            ]\n        )\n\n    course_listings.admin_order_field = \"course_listings\"\n\n    def primary_listing(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Returns the best course department and number string.\n        \"\"\"\n        return unicode(self.course_listing_set.all().get(is_primary=True))\n\n    def __unicode__(self):\n        # + ' ' + ': ' + self.title\n        return \" / \".join(\n            [\n                unicode(course_listing)\n                for course_listing in self.course_listing_set.all().order_by(\"dept\")\n            ]\n        )\n\n    class Meta:\n        pass\n\n    # ordering = ['semester', 'course_listings']\n\n\nclass Section(models.Model):\n    # Types\n    TYPE_CLASS = \"CLA\"\n    TYPE_DRILL = \"DRI\"\n    TYPE_EAR = \"EAR\"\n    TYPE_FILM = \"FIL\"\n    TYPE_LAB = \"LAB\"\n    TYPE_LECTURE = \"LEC\"\n    TYPE_PRECEPT = \"PRE\"\n    TYPE_SEMINAR = \"SEM\"\n    TYPE_STUDIO = \"STU\"\n\n    TYPE_CHOICES = (\n        (TYPE_CLASS, \"class\"),\n        (TYPE_DRILL, \"drill\"),\n        (TYPE_EAR, \"ear training\"),\n        (TYPE_FILM, \"film\"),\n        (TYPE_LAB, \"lab\"),\n        (TYPE_LECTURE, \"lecture\"),\n        (TYPE_PRECEPT, \"precept\"),\n        (TYPE_SEMINAR, \"seminar\"),\n        (TYPE_STUDIO, \"studio\"),\n    )\n\n    # relationships\n    course = models.ForeignKey(\n        Course, related_name=\"sections\", on_delete=models.CASCADE\n    )\n\n    # fields\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=100, default=\"\")\n\n    \"\"\" if true, then everyone in the course is automatically enrolled in this section \"\"\"\n    isDefault = models.BooleanField(default=False)\n    section_type = models.CharField(max_length=3, choices=TYPE_CHOICES)\n    section_enrollment = models.IntegerField(default=0)\n    section_capacity = models.IntegerField(default=999)\n    section_registrar_id = models.CharField(max_length=20, default=\"\")\n\n    def __unicode__(self):\n        return self.course.primary_listing() + \" - \" + self.name\n\n    class Meta:\n        ordering = [\"course\", \"name\"]\n\n\nclass Meeting(models.Model):\n    section = models.ForeignKey(\n        Section, related_name=\"meetings\", on_delete=models.CASCADE\n    )\n    start_time = models.CharField(max_length=20)\n    end_time = models.CharField(max_length=20)\n    days = models.CharField(max_length=10)\n    location = models.CharField(max_length=50)\n\n    def __unicode__(self):\n        return unicode(self.section) + \" - \" + self.location\n\n\nclass Course_Listing(models.Model):\n    course = models.ForeignKey(\n        Course, related_name=\"course_listing_set\", on_delete=models.CASCADE\n    )\n    # Even though the max_length should be 3~4, there are extreme cases.\n    dept = models.CharField(max_length=10)\n    number = models.CharField(max_length=10)\n    is_primary = models.BooleanField(default=False)\n\n    def __unicode__(self):\n        return self.dept + \" \" + self.number\n\n    class Meta:\n        ordering = [\"dept\", \"number\"]\n\n\nclass Major(models.Model):\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=100)\n    code = models.CharField(max_length=7)\n    degree = models.CharField(max_length=3)\n    supported = models.BooleanField(default=False)\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"{self.code} ({self.degree})\"\n\n\nclass UserProfile(models.Model):\n    user = models.OneToOneField(User, on_delete=models.CASCADE, related_name=\"profile\")\n    nickname = models.CharField(max_length=50, null=True, blank=True)\n    major = models.ForeignKey(\n        Major, related_name=\"+\", on_delete=models.CASCADE, null=True\n    )\n    year = models.PositiveSmallIntegerField(null=True)\n    user_state = JSONField(null=True, blank=True)\n    user_schedule = JSONField(null=True, blank=True)\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"{self.user.username}\"\n\n\nclass UserProfileAdmin(admin.ModelAdmin):\n    search_fields = [\"user__username\"]\n\n\n@receiver(post_save, sender=User)\ndef create_user_profile(sender, instance, created, **kwargs):\n    if created:\n        profile = UserProfile.objects.create(\n            user=instance, user_state={\"onboarding_complete\": False}\n        )",

    "/tigerpath/scraper/mobileapp.py": "# ----------------------------------------------------------------------\n# mobileapp.py\n# Contains MobileApp, a class used to communicate with the MobileApp API\n# from the Princeton OIT.\n# Credit: vr2amesh https://github.com/vr2amesh/COS333-API-Code-Examples\n# ----------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nimport requests\nimport json\nimport base64\nfrom os import environ\nimport sys\n\n\nCONSUMER_KEY = environ[\"CONSUMER_KEY\"]\nCONSUMER_SECRET = environ[\"CONSUMER_SECRET\"]\n\n\nclass MobileApp:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.configs = Configs()\n\n    # wrapper function for _getJSON with the courses/courses endpoint.\n    # kwargs must contain key \"term\" with the current term code, as well\n    # as one or more of \"subject\" (department code) and \"search\" (course\n    # title)\n\n    def get_courses(self, **kwargs):\n        kwargs[\"fmt\"] = \"json\"\n        return self._getJSON(self.configs.COURSE_COURSES, **kwargs)\n\n    # wrapper function for _getJSON with the courses/details endpoint.\n    # kwargs must contain key \"term\" with the current term code, as well\n    # as \"course_id\"\n\n    def get_course_details(self, **kwargs):\n        kwargs[\"fmt\"] = \"json\"\n        return self._getJSON(self.configs.COURSE_DETAILS, **kwargs)\n\n    # returns a commma-separated string of all department codes\n\n    def get_all_dept_codes_csv(self):\n        data = self._getJSON(self.configs.COURSE_COURSES, \"subject=list\")\n        return \",\".join([e[\"code\"] for e in data[\"term\"][0][\"subjects\"]])\n\n    # returns a raw JSON of all department codes\n\n    def get_all_dept_codes_json(self):\n        return self._getJSON(self.configs.COURSE_COURSES, \"subject=list\")\n\n    # wrapper function for _getJSON with the courses/terms endpoint.\n    # takes no arguments.\n\n    def get_terms(self):\n        return self._getJSON(self.configs.COURSE_TERMS, fmt=\"json\")\n\n    # generates the n_recent_terms (default 3) most recent term codes\n\n    def get_active_term_codes(self, n_recent_terms=3):\n        def construct_prev_term_code(curr):\n            # curr is Spring, so just change last digit\n            if curr[-1] == \"4\":\n                return curr[:-1] + \"2\"\n\n            # curr is Fall, so decrement middle two digits and change last digit\n            year = curr[1:3]\n            new_year = str(int(year) - 1)\n            return \"1\" + new_year + \"4\"\n\n        if n_recent_terms < 1:\n            raise Exception(\"n_recent_terms must be >= 1\")\n\n        res = self.get_terms()\n        try:\n            term_codes = [res[\"term\"][0][\"code\"]]\n            curr = term_codes[0]\n            for _ in range(n_recent_terms - 1):\n                prev_term_code = construct_prev_term_code(curr)\n                term_codes.append(prev_term_code)\n                curr = prev_term_code\n            term_codes.reverse()\n            return [str(e) for e in term_codes]\n        except:\n            return []\n\n    \"\"\"\n    This function allows a user to make a request to \n    a certain endpoint, with the BASE_URL of \n    https://api.princeton.edu:443/mobile-app\n\n    The parameters kwargs are keyword arguments. It\n    symbolizes a variable number of arguments \n    \"\"\"\n\n    def _getJSON(self, endpoint, **kwargs):\n        req = requests.get(\n            self.configs.BASE_URL + endpoint,\n            params=kwargs if \"kwargs\" not in kwargs else kwargs[\"kwargs\"],\n            headers={\"Authorization\": \"Bearer \" + self.configs.ACCESS_TOKEN},\n        )\n        text = req.text\n\n        # Check to see if the response failed due to invalid credentials\n        text = self._updateConfigs(text, endpoint, **kwargs)\n        print(text)\n        sys.stdout.flush()\n        return json.loads(text)\n\n    def _updateConfigs(self, text, endpoint, **kwargs):\n        if text.startswith(\"<ams:fault\"):\n            self.configs._refreshToken(grant_type=\"client_credentials\")\n\n            # Redo the request with the new access token\n            req = requests.get(\n                self.configs.BASE_URL + endpoint,\n                params=kwargs if \"kwargs\" not in kwargs else kwargs[\"kwargs\"],\n                headers={\"Authorization\": \"Bearer \" + self.configs.ACCESS_TOKEN},\n            )\n            text = req.text\n\n        return text\n\n\nclass Configs:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.CONSUMER_KEY = CONSUMER_KEY\n        self.CONSUMER_SECRET = CONSUMER_SECRET\n        self.BASE_URL = \"https://api.princeton.edu:443/student-app/1.0.1\"\n        self.COURSE_COURSES = \"/courses/courses\"\n        self.COURSE_DETAILS = \"/courses/details\"\n        self.COURSE_TERMS = \"/courses/terms\"\n        self.REFRESH_TOKEN_URL = \"https://api.princeton.edu:443/token\"\n        self._refreshToken(grant_type=\"client_credentials\")\n\n    def _refreshToken(self, **kwargs):\n        req = requests.post(\n            self.REFRESH_TOKEN_URL,\n            data=kwargs,\n            headers={\n                \"Authorization\": \"Basic \"\n                + base64.b64encode(\n                    bytes(self.CONSUMER_KEY + \":\" + self.CONSUMER_SECRET, \"utf-8\")\n                ).decode(\"utf-8\")\n            },\n        )\n        text = req.text\n        response = json.loads(text)\n        self.ACCESS_TOKEN = response[\"access_token\"]\n\n\ndef main():\n    api = MobileApp()\n    # print(api.get_courses(term=\"1224\", search=\"COS333\"))\n    # print(api.get_courses(term=\"1232\", subject=\"AMS,COS\"))\n    print(api.get_active_term_codes(n_recent_terms=8))\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()",
    "/tigerpath/scraper/scrape_all.py": "from django.conf import settings\nfrom django.db import connection\nfrom tigerpath.scraper import scrape_parse, scrape_validate, scrape_import\n\n\ndef get_all_courses():\n    # we can generate these given settings.CURR_TERM\n    term_code = settings.ACTIVE_TERMS[-1]\n    try:\n        print(\"Scraping for semester \" + str(term_code))\n        courses = scrape_parse.scrape_parse_semester(term_code)\n\n        print(\"Validating courses\")\n        for course in courses:\n            scrape_validate.validate_course(\n                course\n            )  # just a sanity check in case we ever modify scrape_parse\n\n        print(\"Updating database\")\n        scrape_counter = scrape_import.ScrapeCounter()\n        length = len(courses)\n        for index, course in enumerate(courses):\n            print(\"Updating course {} of {}\".format(index + 1, length))\n            for _ in range(3):\n                try:\n                    scrape_import.scrape_import_course(course, scrape_counter)\n                except Exception as e:\n                    connection.connection.close()\n                    connection.connection = None\n                    print(\"Updating course {} failed, retrying...\".format(course))\n                    print(e)\n                else:\n                    break\n            else:\n                print(\"Updating course {} failed\".format(course))\n\n        print(str(scrape_counter))\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise e",
    "/tigerpath/scraper/scrape_dist_areas.py": "#!/usr/bin/env python\n\"\"\"\nPython routines for scraping data from Princeton's registrar.\nby Alex Ogier '13.\n\nKept limping along by Brian Kernighan, with bandaids every year\nas the registrar makes format changes.\n\nModified by TigerPath Team\n\"\"\"\n\nimport re\nimport urllib.request\nfrom http.client import RemoteDisconnected\nfrom bs4 import BeautifulSoup\n\nURL_PREFIX = \"http://registrar.princeton.edu/course-offerings/\"\nCOURSE_URL = URL_PREFIX + \"course_details.xml?courseid={courseid}&term={term}\"\nCOURSE_URL_REGEX = re.compile(r\"courseid=(?P<id>\\d+)\")\n\n\ndef clean(str):\n    \"\"\"Return a string with leading and trailing whitespace gone and all other whitespace condensed to a single space.\"\"\"\n    return re.sub(\"\\s+\", \" \", str.strip())\n\n\ndef get_course_details(soup):\n    \"\"\"Returns a dict of {courseid, area}.\"\"\"\n\n    area = clean(soup(\"strong\")[1].findAllNext(text=True)[1])  # balanced on a pinhead\n    if re.match(r\"^\\((LA|SA|HA|EM|EC|QR|STN|STL)\\)$\", area):\n        area = area[1:-1]\n    else:\n        area = \"\"\n\n    return {\n        \"courseid\": COURSE_URL_REGEX.search(\n            soup.find(\"a\", href=COURSE_URL_REGEX)[\"href\"]\n        ).group(\"id\"),\n        \"area\": area,  # bwk: this was wrong[1:-1],    # trim parens #  match.group(1) if match != None else ''\n    }\n\n\ndef scrape_page(page):\n    \"\"\"Returns a dict containing as much course info as possible from the HTML contained in page.\"\"\"\n    soup = BeautifulSoup(page, \"lxml\").find(\n        \"div\", id=\"timetable\"\n    )  # was contentcontainer\n    course = get_course_details(soup)\n    return course\n\n\ndef scrape_id(id, TERM_CODE):\n    for _ in range(3):\n        try:\n            page = urllib.request.urlopen(\n                COURSE_URL.format(term=TERM_CODE, courseid=id)\n            )\n            return scrape_page(page)\n        except RemoteDisconnected as e:\n            print(\"Retrying scraping course id {}\".format(id))\n            print(e)\n        else:\n            break\n    else:\n        raise Exception(\"Scraping course id {} failed\".format(id))",
    "/tigerpath/scraper/scrape_import.py": "from tigerpath.models import Course, Course_Listing, Semester\nfrom tigerpath.scraper.scrape_dist_areas import scrape_id\n\n\nclass ScrapeCounter:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.total_courses_count = 0\n        self.created_courses_count = 0\n        self.total_listings_count = 0\n        self.created_listings_count = 0\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return (\n            str(self.created_courses_count)\n            + \" new courses\\n\"\n            + str(self.total_courses_count)\n            + \" total courses\\n\"\n            + str(self.created_listings_count)\n            + \" new listings\\n\"\n            + str(self.total_listings_count)\n            + \" total listings\"\n        )\n\n\ndef _create_course(course, course_id, counter):\n    course_object, created = Course.objects.get_or_create(\n        registrar_id=course_id,\n        defaults={\"semester\": _create_semester(course[\"semester\"])},\n    )\n    if created:\n        counter.created_courses_count += 1\n    counter.total_courses_count += 1\n    return (course_object, created)\n\n\ndef _create_course_listing(listing, course_object, counter):\n    _, created = Course_Listing.objects.get_or_create(\n        course=course_object,\n        dept=listing[\"dept\"],\n        number=listing[\"code\"],\n        is_primary=listing[\"is_primary\"],\n    )\n    if created:\n        counter.created_listings_count += 1\n    counter.total_listings_count += 1\n\n\ndef _create_semester(semester):\n    semester_object, _ = Semester.objects.get_or_create(\n        term_code=semester[\"term_code\"],\n        defaults={\n            \"start_date\": semester[\"start_date\"],\n            \"end_date\": semester[\"end_date\"],\n        },\n    )\n    return semester_object\n\n\ndef _append_to_all_semesters(term_code, course_object):\n    year = int(term_code[1:3])\n    new_semester_code = (\n        \"f{}\".format(year - 1) if term_code[3] == \"2\" else \"s{}\".format(year)\n    )\n    if new_semester_code not in course_object.all_semesters:\n        course_object.all_semesters.append(new_semester_code)\n\n\ndef _set_cross_listings(listings, course_object):\n    cross_listings = []\n    for l in listings:\n        listing_name = l[\"dept\"] + l[\"code\"]\n        if l[\"is_primary\"]:\n            cross_listings.insert(0, listing_name)\n        else:\n            cross_listings.append(listing_name)\n    course_object.cross_listings = \" / \".join(cross_listings)\n\n\ndef scrape_import_course(course, counter=ScrapeCounter()):\n    term_code = course[\"guid\"][:4]\n    course_id = course[\"guid\"][4:]\n\n    # create course object\n    course_object, course_created = _create_course(course, course_id, counter)\n\n    # set title, description, all_semesters\n    course_object.title = course[\"title\"]\n    course_object.description = course[\"description\"]\n    _append_to_all_semesters(term_code, course_object)\n\n    # add distribution area\n    course_object.dist_area = course[\"distribution_area\"]\n\n    # create course listings\n    for listing in course[\"course_listings\"]:\n        _create_course_listing(listing, course_object, counter)\n\n    # set cross_listings\n    _set_cross_listings(course[\"course_listings\"], course_object)\n\n    course_object.save()\n\n    return counter",

    "/tigerpath/scraper/scrape_validate.py": "class _ValidateError(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, value):\n        self.value = value\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return repr(self.value)\n\n\ndef validate_course(course):\n    def validate_string(item):\n        if item is None or not isinstance(item, str):\n            raise _ValidateError(str(item) + \" is not a string\")\n\n    def validate_string_upper(item):\n        validate_string(item)\n        if not item.isupper():\n            raise _ValidateError(item + \" is not upper case\")\n\n    def validate_boolean(item):\n        if not isinstance(item, bool):\n            raise _ValidateError(item + \" is not a boolean value\")\n\n    def validate_string_not_empty(item):\n        validate_string(item)\n        if len(item) == 0:\n            raise _ValidateError(\"String is empty\")\n\n    def validate_string_max_length(item, length):\n        validate_string(item)\n        if len(item) > length:\n            raise _ValidateError(\n                \"String \" + item + \" exceeded max length of \" + str(length)\n            )\n\n    def validate_dict(dict, rules):\n        for key, validator in rules.items():\n            try:\n                validator(dict[key])\n            except _ValidateError as e:\n                raise _ValidateError(key + \": \" + str(e))\n\n    def validate_array(array, validator):\n        for x in array:\n            validator(x)\n\n    semester_validator = {\n        \"start_date\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"end_date\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"term_code\": validate_string_not_empty,\n    }\n\n    professor_validator = {\n        \"full_name\": validate_string_not_empty,\n    }\n\n    listing_validator = {\n        \"dept\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"code\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"is_primary\": validate_boolean,\n    }\n\n    meeting_validator = {\n        \"start_time\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"end_time\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"days\": lambda x: validate_string_max_length(x, 10),\n        \"location\": validate_string,\n    }\n\n    section_validator = {\n        \"registrar_id\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"name\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"type\": lambda x: validate_string_max_length(x, 3) and validate_string_upper(x),\n        \"capacity\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"enrollment\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"meetings\": lambda array: validate_array(\n            array, lambda meeting: validate_dict(meeting, meeting_validator)\n        ),\n    }\n\n    course_validator = {\n        \"title\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"guid\": validate_string_not_empty,\n        \"description\": validate_string,\n        \"distribution_area\": validate_string,\n        \"semester\": lambda x: validate_dict(x, semester_validator),\n        \"professors\": lambda array: validate_array(\n            array, lambda prof: validate_dict(prof, professor_validator)\n        ),\n        \"course_listings\": lambda array: validate_array(\n            array, lambda listing: validate_dict(listing, listing_validator)\n        ),\n        \"sections\": lambda array: validate_array(\n            array, lambda section: validate_dict(section, section_validator)\n        ),\n    }\n    validate_dict(course, course_validator)",

About</title>\n\n    <!-- Bootstrap core CSS -->\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.0.0/css/bootstrap.min.css\" integrity=\"sha384-Gn5384xqQ1aoWXA+058RXPxPg6fy4IWvTNh0E263XmFcJlSAwiGgFAW/dAiS6JXm\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\">\n\n    <!-- Custom fonts for this template -->\n    <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300,400,700,300italic,400italic,700italic\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\">\n\n    <!-- Custom styles for this template -->\n    <link href=\"{% static 'landing/css/landing-page.css' %}\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n\n    {% include 'includes/analytics/analytics_head.html' %}\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    {% include 'includes/analytics/analytics_body.html' %}\n\n    {% include 'includes/navigation.html' %}\n\n    <div class=\"header-bg\"></div>\n\n    <section class=\"container mb-4 mt-5\">\n      <h2 class=\"text-center mb-4\">About TigerPath</h2>\n\n      <div class=\"text-section\">\n        <p>TigerPath is a web application that helps Princeton University students plan out their four-year course schedules.</p>\n        <p>We built TigerPath because we saw a need for Princeton students to have a tool that could help them think long-term about what courses to take and how to fulfill their graduation requirements.</p>\n        <p>Many students try to manually manage what courses to take and when to take them by using an Excel spreadsheet or pen-and-paper, but any mistake can easily lead to an overloaded semester or a need to take summer classes in order to fulfill missed requirements.</p>\n        <p>TigerPath aims to solve this problem by providing a platform for students to manage what courses they're taking during each semester and giving them real-time feedback on the major requirements their schedule fulfills and does not fulfill. Our goal is for TigerPath to become a useful, enduring tool that ensures Princeton students are able to stay on top of requirements and graduate on time.</p>\n        <p>The <a href=\"https://www.tigerapps.org\" target=\"_blank\">TigerApps Team</a> actively maintains and upgrades TigerPath.</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"text-section\">\n        <h4>Team Members</h4>\n        <div>Richard Chu - rc11@</div>\n        <div>Barak Nehoran - bnehoran@</div>\n        <div>Adeniji Ogunlana - ogunlana@</div>\n        <div>Daniel Leung - dl13@</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"text-section\">\n        <h4>Acknowledgments</h4>\n        <p class=\"mb-0\">J\u00e9r\u00e9mie Lumbroso - COS 333 Spring 2018 Advisor</p>\n        <p>Brian Kernighan - COS 333 Spring 2018 Professor</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"text-section\">\n        <h4>Resources</h4>\n        <p class=\"mb-0\"><a href=\"{% static 'res/tigerpath_design_doc.pdf' %}\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Design Document</a></p>\n        <p class=\"mb-0\"><a href=\"{% static 'res/report.pdf' %}\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Report</a></p>\n        <p><a href=\"{% static 'res/productguide.pdf' %}\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Product Guide</a></p>\n      </div>\n    </section>\n\n    {% include 'includes/footer.html' %}\n  </body>\n</html>",

In order to provide you with this service, we gather certain kinds of data from Princeton University and from you (the user). We also use some third-party services that could gather data about you. </p>\n        <p>We are committed to protecting your privacy, and we try to be as transparent as possible about how we handle data in TigerPath. The purpose of this privacy policy is to help you understand what kinds of data we collect and what we use them for.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"text-section\">\n        <h4>Authentication</h4>\n        <p>We protect the entire application underneath CAS authentication, which is the same system you use to sign into other Princeton services, like TigerHub.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"text-section\">\n        <h4>User Data</h4>\n        <p>Your data is stored securely. We will never give or sell your data to third parties, or allow other users or nonusers access to your data without your explicit permission. We only store the data that we need to in order to provide you with the best experience possible in TigerPath. This data includes your nickname, class year, major, and four-year course schedule. By using TigerPath, you are consenting to the storage of this data.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"text-section\">\n        <h4>University Data</h4>\n        <p>We collect the course listings data from the OIT Web Feed Registry and the Course Offerings webpage, and we compile the requirements information from the Princeton University Undergraduate Announcement website and the official Princeton University department websites.</p>\n        <p>Although we endeavor to make the displayed course listings and requirements information as accurate as possible, we make no guarantees about the accuracy of our data. The definitive word will always come from the university administration and departments, and you should verify with them if you are in doubt about the veracity of any university data on our app. We would also appreciate it if you <a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/T0pnhwdBYIS8mM6q1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">notify us</a> about any errors you find.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"text-section\">\n        <h4>Third-Party Services</h4>\n        <p>We use some third-party services that help us improve your experience in the app:</p>\n        <ul>\n          <li>TigerBook API, to automatically populate your name, class year, and major.</li>\n          <li>Google Analytics, to collect aggregated anonymous metadata on how you use the app so we can continually improve it.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </section>\n\n    {% include 'includes/footer.html' %}\n  </body>\n</html>",

    "/tigerpath/urls.py": "from django.urls import path\nfrom . import views\n\nurlpatterns = [\n    # app urls\n    path(\"\", views.index, name=\"index\"),\n    path(\"landing\", views.landing, name=\"landing\"),\n    path(\"about\", views.about, name=\"about\"),\n    path(\"privacy\", views.privacy_policy, name=\"privacy_policy\"),\n    path(\"onboarding/save\", views.save_onboarding, name=\"save_onboarding\"),\n    path(\"settings/save\", views.save_user_settings, name=\"save_settings\"),\n    # cas auth\n    path(\"login\", views.login, name=\"login\"),\n    path(\"logout\", views.logout, name=\"logout\"),\n    # api\n    path(\"api/v1/get_courses/<search_query>\", views.get_courses, name=\"get_courses\"),\n    path(\"api/v1/get_courses/\", views.get_courses, name=\"get_courses\"),\n    path(\"api/v1/update_schedule/\", views.update_schedule, name=\"update_schedule\"),\n    path(\"api/v1/get_schedule/\", views.get_schedule, name=\"get_schedule\"),\n    path(\"api/v1/get_requirements/\", views.get_requirements, name=\"get_requirements\"),\n    path(\n        \"api/v1/get_req_courses/<req_path>\",\n        views.get_req_courses,\n        name=\"get_req_courses\",\n    ),\n    path(\"api/v1/get_profile/\", views.get_profile, name=\"get_profile\"),\n    path(\n        \"api/v1/update_schedule_and_get_requirements/\",\n        views.update_schedule_and_get_requirements,\n        name=\"update_schedule_and_get_requirements\",\n    ),\n]",
    "/tigerpath/utils.py": "from base64 import b64encode\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport os\nimport hashlib\nimport requests\n\nTIGERBOOK_BASE_URL = \"https://tigerbook.herokuapp.com/api/v1/undergraduates/\"\n\n# DO NOT CALL THIS METHOD WHILE TIGERBOOK API IS DOWN.\n# Get information about the student with the specified netid from Tigerbook\ndef get_student_info(netid):\n    url = TIGERBOOK_BASE_URL + netid\n    r = requests.get(url, headers=create_tigerbook_wsse_headers())\n    return r.json() if r.status_code == 200 else None\n\n\n# Helper function that creates Tigerbook WSSE headers for the request\n# See https://github.com/alibresco/tigerbook-api to get api key\ndef create_tigerbook_wsse_headers():\n    created = datetime.utcnow().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\")\n    nonce = b64encode(os.urandom(32)).decode()\n    username = os.getenv(\"TIGERBOOK_USERNAME\")\n    password = os.getenv(\"TIGERBOOK_API_KEY\")\n    hash_arg = (nonce + created + password).encode()\n    generated_digest = b64encode(hashlib.sha256(hash_arg).digest()).decode()\n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": 'WSSE profile=\"UsernameToken\"',\n        \"X-WSSE\": 'UsernameToken Username=\"{}\", PasswordDigest=\"{}\", Nonce=\"{}\", Created=\"{}\"'.format(\n            username, generated_digest, b64encode(nonce.encode()).decode(), created\n        ),\n    }\n    return headers"
}
